restaurants.Cuisines: Healthy Food, Juices, Fast Food, Salad
restaurants.address: Shop No.9, Nand Kripa Shopping Near Ganesh sai dham ,Ratan Nagar corner, Gharkul Society, Ratan Nagar, Four Bungalows, Andheri West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400053, India

reviews.text: Ordered brown rice with paneer makhani from Pishus four bunglow branch .Best veg dish ever had with exotic veggies in gravy with brown rice. the taste was truly delicious. Food was deliciously healthy.i assure if someone has love for continental and if they will have this dish they will surely love it and will recommend others to try.

Pishu's is a great place to have healthy food. 
Details of the food like it's calories and protein content are mentioned in the menu which helps you to keep a track on your calories and protein intake. 
Food is very tasty and service is very fast.
A healthy take on fast food. Really delicious, at the same time guilt free healthy food. Value for money

The outlet serves healthy food. They even have mamy detox juices. Check the menu for more details. They even have mentioned the tentative number of calories in their each dish.
.
I ordered the Burnt Garlic pizza. The base is replaced with multi grain cracker. You can even replace the cheese with paneer. The taste is awesome with burnt garlic taste and crispy cracker as it's base. This is something new. Must try.
.
Next ordered pasta garlic cheese - this is not for people who love cheesy white pasta. As it has many vegetables and it is not very cheesy. It is healthy pasta. Whole wheat penne pasta with broccoli, jalapeno, zucchini, olives etc. The pasta is accompanied by lavash crackers. Loved this too. Crispy cracker with white pasta :) :D
.
There are many seasonal juices too. They have even mentioned the benefits of the fruits used in the juice. Loved the concept of healthy food. Must try if you are health consious. :)

They offer healthy drinks and food. I ordered Green Effect juice and Hummus Platter. The juice was pretty good while the platter was below average. The salad and hummus did not taste great. 

I feel that some of the items in the menu are healthy for name sake. For example, they have healthy pizza on their menu. I have no clue what is so healthy about Pizza.

The service is pretty good. Waiting time is pretty low. Overall hygiene of the place is good.

Its a great place to have a quick refreshing fruit juices and shakes.

restaurants.address: Shop No 17, Rainbow Tower, Sri Sadguru Vamanrao Pai Marg, Sector-19, Airoli, Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra 400708, India

reviews.text:
A unique place to have a brunch or go with friends for dineout !
This restaurant has no waiters, you give your order to a machine belt and that's how you place an order. 
Offers various dishes with starters and beverages on the side. Pocket friendly place with a nice ambience. 
The idea of placing order is quiet unique ! 
Must Have : volcano pizza and Salsa Fries.
Not good to dine..in post pandemic time as place is crowded by swiggy-Zomato boys

Bruciato food factory

Bff is a small and cute cafe nestled in airoli sector 19.the menu is very well curated with lip refreshing drinks , shakes ... good place to try new stuff and it is very affordable..

Ambiance
The interior is pretty and simple..having a decent and beautiful ambiance with indoor.

Food
The menu offers huge varieties of burgers and pizza to choose from , difficult fusion also they have variety in fries ,pasta , desert etc.

This place is the best for college students to hang out. The prices are very reasonable and the food is very good and worth the price. The way of ordering is different here as there goes a chain above us and we have to attach our order to it which goes directly to the kitchen. The concept of the place is different and the music is also good and in all it feels like a great place to go to in a reasonable price.

Concept wise it was something different, there is a nice chain running above your head (consists of Christmas gifts, your orders and a times bills too).
We ordered :
Veg nachos - quite great blend of veggies, cheese, mayo and perfect sauce dip made it complete.
Cold coffee - nice texture and taste
Peach ice tea - this one was kind of okayish, considering the amount of extra sugar it had. Apart from that the tea was cool.

Ambience - 4/5
Hospitality - 4/5
Food,taste and texture - 4/5
Overall - 4/5

restaurants.address: Shop no. 2, roadBesides Mauli Sports, Ramdas Apartment, Mulund - Airoli Rd, Diva Gaothan, Sector 9, Airoli, Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra 400708, India

reviews.text:
Well while my favourite football team was getting beaten there was something saved my day...ofcuz it was Pizza but this made me forget my embarrassment. Ever since I'm in love with this outlet...
Something I love to order...

1. Double Cheese Margarita pizza
2. Smokey Joe Pizza
3. Tandoori Chicken Wing

Quality Pizza, delivered hot & fresh at your door-step.
Mojo  Pizza  is one of the delivery pizza joint that offer many different selections of fresh delicious pizzas .

So what did we have?
 
• MEAT EATER (big 10 inch NON -VEG pizza)

If you are a meat-eater & you haven’t tried a Meat Eater pizza, then it’s safe to say you are missing out on something special. 
Loaded with Bbq chicken, Roast Chicken, Chicken Keema, Chicken Sausage to this pizza that you are sure to love.

• FIRE ME UP (big 10 inch NON -VEG pizza)

Your best bet if you’re craving for some delicious Spicy Non Veg pizza.
Loaded with fresh cookedBBQ Chicken, Chicken Tikka, Spicy Jalapenos, Baby Corn, this pizza is juicy with every bite.
 
• TEX- MEX SPECIAL (big10 inch VEG pizza)

 Loaded with Red Paprika, Golden Corn, Capsicum & veggies, richly flavorful  salsa sauce. The Tex - Mex vegetarian pizza is a must try for everyone.

Whoever wishes for more toppings and cheese in their pizza fear not coz Mojo Pizza is here.
MOJO pizza in the least year or 2 have gained quite a popularity among all the pizza lovers coz of promise of 2x toppings.

We had:
▪️Garlic bread with cheese dip:
The garlic bread was made and baked well. The cheese dip went great with it. 

▪️Bbq Chicken Pizza:
7 inch pizza topped with BBQ chicken, corn and Jalapeno was made to perfection. The chicken was juicy and the cheese was amazing. 

▪️Classic Pepperoni Pizza:
Generous quantity of cheese was topped with the pepperoni. It was tasty and delicious. 

▪️Butterscotch Blizzard:
New in their dessert menu so gave it a try and was not disappointed. It was very similar to a butterscotch cake and completed out whole meal. 

MOJO always delivers the pizza hot, fresh and on time. It is one of the best places for pizza cravings. 
They also have great offers that continuously goes on which is great.

Another bad experience with Mojo pizza's Instafresh not-at-all "zero contact delivery."

The delivery guy did not sanitize his hands before delivering the items. Mojo does not provide a bag anyways. And the choco lava cake he brought had spilled as it was lying clumsily at the bottom with onions and veggies on top of it. 

I make it a point to wash all the veggies received as they are all touched by hand. Do u expect me to wash the choco lava cake? 
This executive argued that he sanitized his hands at the store. But what about him touching the bike handle and ten other things on the way? 

I want an immediate call back and replacement. 
I am going to share this second horrible experience online on all possible channels (Twitter Facebook and wherever else possible). 

Enough is enough.

After many get together's,I have decided to take a break from every and pampered myself.Its all about me time.i had ordered pizza from Mojo and believe me they were amazing in taste.chicken wings were so juicy and spicy and garlic sticks are crispy and taste good with mayo.The toppings on pizza are very crisp and delicious.

reviews.text: Great place to have food and relax, nice ambiance and friendly staff. Service is good and view is amazing from here, little expensive but not bad for one time experience....!

A perfect romantic getaway restaurant near Mumbai. Great setup. Best time to visit is during sunsets. Music and service is nice. Food options are limited but everything else is fab. Loved the sizzling brownie. The jetty ride to this restaurant is also worth an experience. Must visit for all young couples out thr.

Lovely place right by the jetty, before you pass the container stores and reach the parking. The inside area is comfortable but the sofas outside is the place to be. Good choice and quality of food. 
Wish they had working wifi too.

Been here after hearing the hype for this place.... However live experience wasn't that good... quantity of food is very less n taste is below average but the price we pay is very high including 10% Service charge... however the cocktails are very good & ambience is very refreshing..photogenic place...

A decent place to hang out once you reach alibaug it's right beside where you get down on the jetty. The view has been disturbed due to recent construction. The food and ambiance is decent. The drinks are below average not upto the flamboyante mark. The place is over crowded and always full.
 If you are lucky you'll get a place with a view at the inner most corner.

reviews.text:
Would definitely recommend this place for a foodie. What can i say... What a good food quality and presentation. I loved all the items that were available at the buffet. Staff was well mannered and presentable. Also the service was quick. They had lots of options for deserts. This place is a must go go for offices goers around the place. This resto is inside hotel 
Mirador.

Good food. Not enough range of starters available for vegetarians. Starters for non vegetarians was good. The best I would say would be the fish fry. Nachos and hummus a must try. For main course, dal rice was the best option for vegetarians. Veg spaghetti was also average. For non vegetarians, Hong Kong prawns with gravy was amazing. Desserts very absolutely fantastic and delicious too. Carrot cake with orange is a must try. Also dark chocolate with nuts was very nice. Icecream was good. All in all vegetarians would not be satisfied with the range of food available for them. Good place to visit if you are a non vegetarian. Interior design was also very sleek.

Value for money Buffet spread for non- vegetarians. Limited options for vegetarians.
Awesome deserts. Best part was the live seafood counter serving prawns,squid and bangada fry.

reviews.text: A cute greeny cozy place to hangout. Tue ambience is good . Food taste needs a lot of improvement. The cocktails are not that attractive and tasty. A little expensive than what is served. The staff is courteous polite and cooperative.

Fancy place for corporate fellows to celebrate weekend culture. Ambience is amazing bit expensive. food or average but can go with you gang for weekend enjoyment. this place is stated at the point which is really very easyly accessible. you can visit it once but fairly this place didn't excite me like other sports bar.

#ETCuisine

Craftbar

A Gastropub in the heart of the city is worth visiting. Based in Kalanagar, Bandra, Mumbai. Amazing place to hang out with your friends and colleagues for sure. As it is located in Bandra, near corporate hub of BKC, it is crowded place. But the food and drinks severed here, makes it more crowded. 

The venue is separated in two as lounge and restaurant. Continuous music will surely make you more relax than ever. Plus, humble staff makes you more comfortable. 

Drinks we ordered are 

Bellini, sparkling wine with blended peach puree. The Seven Island Ice Tea, a perfect mixture of 7 prominent liquors like gin vodka, tequila, rum and juices. Nojito Kiwi, freshly blended kiwi mixed with citrus syrup and minty lemonade. Citrus Cooler (Pineapple), fab mixture of pineapple juice with aerated lemon juice.

Food we ordered are,

Murg Abadhi Tikka, marinated in pickling spices and deep-fried boneless chicken pieces. Lord of The Wings, spice marinated and deep-fried chicken wings. Spaghetti Aglio E Olio, spaghetti noodles pasta cooked in olive oil, garnished with herbs and served in red sauce with chicken. Regular French Fries with tomato ketchup. Cheese cake with sparkle of coco powder as a dessert.

Location: 5/5
Ambiance: 4/5
Cuisine: 5/5
Drinks: 5/5

This place is amazing from outside and from inside 
The food quality is very good and rich 
You can go for plenty of cocktails available in fancy style 
Moctails are also very good here 
But the best thing about this place is its ambiance and desserts 
Desserts have a very beautiful presentation
Staff and manager are very friendly.

CRAFTBAR 
everything in here is quite crafty, be it their tables, chairs, lamps, the handcrafted decor in the walls, and especially their cocktails 
They have a very comfy and cozy seating arrangement for all kinda groups 
They have also got a blissful outdoor seating arrangements 
The staff here are prompt, courteous and through with their menu 
overall amazing ambiance as well as the staff 
but they have got even more amazing food...lets discuss that 

Food Language 

A. Beverages 
   1. The 7 island iced tea:- literally had a mixture of all, a well crafted drink for alcohol lovers, may be the best 
   2. Pinacolada :- White rum infused in pineapple, coconut and vanilla cream which was very soothing and also my most fav 
   3. Spider Bite Shotz :- 2 are served in a chilled glass with vodka infused in lime 
   4. nujito :- aerated minty flavoured have always been my fav so i definitely loved this one as it had a quite unique twist to the mojito 

B. Starters 
   1. Lord Of The Wings :- Delicious crispy chicken Wings tossed in spicy siriracha, a bit oily but worth the taste 
   2. BEER BATTER PRAWNS :- Deep fried crunchy and tender prawns served along with mayo was too awesome to taste, am sure you won't get enough of it 

C. Main Course 
   1. Chicken Molten Lasagna :- This was the first time i had a lasagna and this place made me fall in love with it 
layers of cheese and shredded chicken one above the other a blend of which made the whole totally delectable, i couldn't stop eating it even after i was full 
   2. Khow Suey :- The name is weird but the dish isn't, Fresh veggies cooked in coconut milk coverd with the bed of noodles and pieces of chicken all over had a unique interesting and lovely taste 

D. DESSERT 
   1. Rasgulla Birds Nest :- small Rasgullas  are served in vermicelli nest with rabdi below was ultimately luscious 
   2. Flambeed Kal Jamoon :- Gulab jamoon bathed with flaming rum is served along with ice-cream a blend which was made to be quite piquant 
overall Had marvellous experience in here

Krishna Restaurant , a a hidden gem in Bandra East for seafood ,non veg dishes aks Chinese cuisine!! The flavours are amazing here and quanity very filling!!
Coming to what I had :-
Rawas tikka :- This was a soft , extremely Delicious and spicy rawas tikka.The flavours were amazing and that masala was lip smacking!! Highly recommend this dish!

Prawns Rava Fry:-Fried Rava  King Prawns in generous quanity!! Prawns were crispy and very juicy and just loved the Prawns and rawa flavours!!Good enough for three people.Highly recommend!

Kungpao Chicken :- The smell of this dish was wonderful and so was the taste and quanity!!The kungpao sauce was just so amazing and very delicious!!! Chicken was juicy and soft and tasted amazing !

Surmai malwani fry :- This consisted of a medium sized Surmai cooked  in spicy red masala .The surmai was cooked  to perfection!! The Flavours were just Amazing!!Highly Recommend this malwani fried Surmai.

Prawns crispy :- This consisted of king Prawns cooked in red sauce with some Crispy sev which is usually served with soup.Loved the idea and it definitely worked in terms of flavours. Prawns was tasty and with that sev gave that lovely crispy and flavour to it!!

Mutton maratha gravy with garlic naan and missi roti :- This gravy was so appetizing and delightful!! Mutton was soft and pieces were quite good!! Curry was spicy and served hot.Tasted fabulous with garlic naan  and missi roti!! I liked garlic naan more ,it was yummy and lovely with that maratha curry!Highly Recommend this maratha Mutton curry

For desserts we had

Custard:- This was a lovely custard with a god consistency and texture.Jiggly and sweet it looked good.Tasted Yummy!
Rabdi :- This was one of the best rabdi I ever had.Had the perfect sweetness and texture!! Cold and lovely ended my meal on a perfect note!

Good food,but   below Average service, ordered for kebabs was told after 20mins that's not available,  suggested a different kebab which took a hour to come, had to wait for the order for more than hour hungry.  Killed our appetite for the food.

Recently visited Krishna restaurant in Bandra.food was too good there,i was looking for good restaurant I found this i order butter chicken and kebabs was too pretty.if you are looking for good Chinese Indian dishes this restaurant is perfect..guys to visit this place.....

FOOD 5/5
AMBIENCE 4/5
SERVICE 5/5
STAFF 5/5

The Place is located nearby Chetna College Bandra East. Speaking of ambience it is perfect place where you can spend quality time with you family and friends. The pleasent and look lights will definitely wins your hearts. The food is mind blowing. The starters were superb, The garnishing of the food is perfect. Talking about the presentation actually I am speechless bcoz I have never seen this perfection.
The service given was equivalent to a 5 start hotel service. The waiters were claim and ready to help and it was quite good to have dine there. The prices were also pocket friendly. Talking about the quantity and quality it is worth the price. I wonder how difficult it must be for them to be consistent, but the fact is that they are consistent when it comes to taste.

reviews.text: I didn't just like the food, I absolutely loved it! It's a great setting for dining with family or for chilling with friends. Versatile that way. It has a bar, but age restrictions are only during the evenings. Enjoyed most of the dishes here. Nice ambience. Oh and unique part: the menu. The dishes so wisely named. You'll enjoy just reading through the menu, it is such a fun read!

One of the best places in BKC, we had been here for Dinner. 
The ambience is good. Comfortable sitting. The staff is friendly. The food is good and hygienic. 
The starters were good. In the main course, loved the Mutton grave. 
The Desserts were also very nice. 
Overall the presentation of all dishes was very appealing.

Loved the place, will surely visit again.

Right setting that sets the right mood. Funky Menu titles will attract your attention. Food quality is good and served in good portions. Service is bit slow. Entire seating is on single floor at same level. Overall a good hangout place to chill with friends and families.

Ambiance is good. Crowd is decent, you will find more Oldies here. Drink options are great and the cocktails were amazing. The staff is not that great, they tend to ignore you sometimes when it is busy. The location is perfect, bang in the middle of BKC. Food is average at best, did not like the snacks we ordered. Prices are like most other pubs, could have been a tad bit lower, but I won't complain.
It is a good place to chill with your friends. You'll get those bollywood feels as soon as you enter this place. The food menu was very exciting as it was a fusion of Indian and global cuisines.

reviews.text: The restaurant ambience is cool and best place for fine dining. The bar at the entry is high class and display good collection of wine and spirits. Nice place with decent ambience.
Try out their set menu for VEG / NON-VEG
Desserts is a must try!! Chocolate pebble is the best dessert for vegetarians who love dark chocolate
Unique taste , we got to try very new recipes and very delicious... If sumone want to try some delicious authentic Chinese recipe..u have to come here... Beautiful ambience also...

I have been to Yauatcha a couple of times and I do not mind having these meals every single day! 
The servers were very kind and accommodating, always impressed us when we told them to suggest us items from the menu, they knew what was the best! 
The drinks here taste a little bit like heaven, you can't even taste alcohol in the cocktails, that's how good they are! 
Oh and the dumplings? They MELT in your mouth! The chicken coriander dumplings are my favourite, the shrimp fried rice is simply great as well! 
The food looks very appetising, even the way it's served! 
The ambience of the place is good, although it can be a little too loud when it gets full. 
This is definitely one of my favourite restaurants in the city! Can't wait to be back!

Located out of Raheja towers in Bandra Kurla Complex, Bandra East, it is a large property and very spacious with small and large tables, well spaced. Weekends see a huge footfall and if you are a late night reveller with a large group, you might have to wait for your turn.

Service is warm with a decent ambience, could be better as they have a large space. Lighting is soothing and seats are comfortable.

I had been here twice now, once during a weekday and one during a weekend and of course, my experience during the weekday was too good as they would pay every attention to make your visit a pleasurable one. Cocktails and food wouldn't make you complain, they are well done, especially their prawns and duck dishes. As per their cost, the portions are less, however, given the overall experience as a foodie, I would pass it on. Cheers!

reviews.text: Very different food from the other restaurants that I frequent. Exceptional taste, especially the sea food. We had a slice of coffee toffee cheesecake and that was yummy too. Very nice. Assamese pork and Amores cheesecake recommended. Cocktails decent. Good service. Nice for a chilled weekday lunch. Also recommended, given the portion sizes, is not eating for 24 hours before going or you will burst.

Fantastic service, awesome dishes. Definitely reccomend it to someone wanting to try a new place and some different kind of food from normal. Great ambience, presentation of dishes and portion size. Will be coming back again for sure.
I just love bastian ! Specially it’s Sunday brunch is amazing ! I had ordered crispy spiced salt chicken and sesame chicken ! Loved both of them. It’s a must try place

reviews.text: Since the ownership has changed the place has become a disaster the food was terrible and they are not doing justice to their beautiful ambience.
Awesome place. But they should maintain aquarium. I saw they don’t clean aquarium properly.
Had Kolhapur Vada Pav. It is delicious and worth trying it.

Cafe Hydro is such an outlet which really blows your mind off , the multi cusine restaurant really surprises you as soon as you step right in .
It's a 3 floor  restaurant, and each floor is dedicated to a certain theme .
The outlet in whole is Aqua themed.
So the ground floor is  themed after  Mumbai's lifeline i.e. Local trains .
Even the flooring is upon railway track.
And seating is designed like train seating the props are the rack where luggage is kept.
It is very detailed execution.
The first floor is about ocean ,Also what amazes here is that the walls here are of one huge fish tank , which just really makes it more beautiful. Its very lavish.
The second floor is garden theme, even this has fish tank in one side, but the seating here changes and there are cloth swings , various masks are stick on wall. The lighting and everything makes it so soothing. Cute seating area and whole concept makes it soo amazing!! 
It even has 3 different kind of seating.
Talking about the food , we had an amazing experience.

Here's what we had ?

🔶 Dynamite :-

This was a 3 layered juice which had 3 different layers , and it was very nicely presented taste was also perfect and refreshing.

🔷 Spicy Guava :-

This is our all time favorite mocktail but this was quite actually more spicy.

🔶 Chicken Manchow Soup :-

The soup was great , it was spicy and also the chicken pieces were big enough. The flavor of ginger , garlic and chilly was strong , 
Only it was may more thick 

🔷 Chicken Zaffrani Tikka :-

Pieces of chicken perfectly marinated and cooked , which had an amazing smoky taste is all you need as a perfect appetizer.

🔶 Chilly Chicken Dry :-

Presentation of this was good , fried chicken pieces with an amazing marination tossed with a Little sauce and not loosing it's cripsyness. Taste was good it was spicy.

🔷 Burnt Garlic Chicken Rice :-

This is usually our favorite item , but here it was tasting quite bitter in between. Quantity was very good .

🔶Brownie with Ice Cream & Ice Cream:-

Brownie with ice cream is something which we always prefer and this is  best part of any meal it was really good , even we took only ice cream, 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream rich and full filling.

Taste :-⭐⭐⭐⭐
Price :-⭐⭐⭐⭐
Staff & Service :-⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Ambience:-⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐( it's really great )
Value for money :-⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

✔️ Every worth penny ambience.

✔️ Great food and good service 

✔️ Perfect for quality time with friends and family.

So Cafe Hydro is such an outlet which you cannot miss !! We recommend you to visit in the evening, to enjoy the ambience❤

reviews.text:
The best part about this place is LIVE MUSIC. It is simply marvelous , multiple drinking option and it is vegetarian restaurant with quite Jain option available.. Live music is basically on weekends so plan it accordingly rest of the time DJ rocks.. it has multiple seating option as per your convenience.
I'm definitely going to visit this place again as the vibes about the place incredible.

Good Live music option restaurant with amazing food. I have visited twice this place. Once on valentines day when it was superbly heavily rushed thus not so good experience in food and staff treating customers. Second time it was all opposite, being moderately occupied they served amazing food. For foodies its worth trying and for live music hunters its worth visiting and chilling 😁

Visited Timess Square for the first time, and the first impression was pretty good... Off beat interiors, Huge infrastructure with 3 storied dining area, a fairly diverse menu, plenty of staff to look after you, good service... And most importantly, Tasty Food with Good Quantity!!! A good place to spend time with your family or friends.... Table reservation recommended since the restaurant is quite popular and buzzing with food lovers!!!

One of the best places in Borivali for some live music and great food. It has 3 sections out of which one is outside seating. They have a variety of dishes to choose from. Also, Zomato gold is applicable here.

It's good place for grabbing some good food and brunch! They have two facilities, a ac hall and open garden restaurant with live music. The band was awesome. Rates of food is bit costly but for the vibes you get here it's justifying. Also it's noticeable from the road in heavy traffic as well. It's good place for weekend evening getaway with good food and music.

reviews.text: One of the best after sales service I've ever received. The food is great as well. A must try for late night snack or your dinner.

One of our friend had uploaded some of the pic's of Food Adda and they looked so yummy!!  We thought it's a must try!! So accordingly we searched on Zomato and went to borivali west outlet...

As decided we went.... The place was damn cool...We just loved the ambiance...it ws very funky.... The staff was very polite...

We ordered the star dishes of the place:

All Star Italian Panini Grilled Sandwich....When the dish arrived...🤤 Our mouth just got sealed...it looked so amazing and when we tasted it... It ws seriously jannat...😋 Highly recommended...!!!

 

The second dish we ordered was Italiano Pizza Fries...it was so cheesy...🧀🧀 ...quantity was also tummy filling..🍟  A must try! 

Both the dishes were worth the money!

This place is located at borivali ! Small place to visit with friends ! They have good menu with various snacks ! 

We ordered - 
1. Chocolate shake 
2. Cheese chilly Sandwich 

Both were good in taste ! Would love to visit again ❤️

Cant Express my disappointment. The owner seems to be a chef in UAE. He doesn't know the quality or quantity that should be served. Don't think you can cover profits by giving the customer half the quantity! Will never ever go to food adda again. Stop cheating!

Food Adda is crowded but a comfy place. If you are craving for something cheesy and delicious then you must visit this place. Our personal favorite here are Peach Mojito a fruity twist with flavours of peach and mint. Jio Cheese Sandwich and Big Burger Pizza are our favorite cheesy delights that we had when visited Food Adda. Really loved the presentation and the taste everything was on point and scrumptious. We concluded our snack with Strawberry With Cream which was rich, creamy and enjoyable.

restaurants.address: 301,The Bombay Cartel, 3rd floor, Hubtown Skybay, Bhulabhai Desai Marg, near Mahalaxmi Temple, Mahalaxmi(W), Breach Candy, Cumballa Hill, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400026, India

reviews.text:
Bombay cartel is the place to visit if you want to have good drink. Long Island Tea was one of the best I have drunk anywhere. Other drinks like Fireball were beautifully presented. Russian Mafia presented in traditional copper mug was good too. In all the cocktails, the alcohol taste was subtle while the punch was still there.
Food wise the fare is ordinary to good, the cheese filled pakodas were good while the salad was barely passable, being too sweet.

The dessert was sinful and amazing to eat. Overall a great place to visit and have evening out.

The Bombay Cartel is located near the famous Mahalaxmi Temple. The name Bombay cartel itself give us a reach feeling about this restaurant. This restaurant is located inside a building where there are more restaurants on the other floors. This restaurant is located on the third floor of the building. This restaurant has a lift to go up to the third floor. As you enter to the third floor you will be in another world this place also has parking facility. The ambience of the place is too good this place have live bar facility so that you can order your drink easily and this place also play matches on a big screen so you can enjoy your drinks with your favorite match streaming live on a big screen. The staffs and the service of the restaurant is good they are good at their service special thanks to Mr. Prabhat and Mr. Priyatam this two steward did not gave any chance of disappointment they ware best at their service. Service was fast and quick the food they serve was just awesome it was fresh and hot also loved the drinks at place you should definitely try Cocktails at this place. And the biggest thing about this place is they serve some of the drinks on MRP which is really amazing. This place has everything you want. There was soft music played in the restaurant which really feels me comfortable. Coming to the food we had.

.

WHAT WE HAD

DRINKS

1)	Sex On The Beach

This was looking to good it was nicely presented and was garnished with orange on top of the drink. This drink was having orange flavor in it the taste was also good.

2)	Polish Cooler

This drink was a vodka base drink which was having cucumis juice and coconut syrup in it. The taste was good it was nicely presented not to strong not to mild it was just perfect.

STARTERS

3)	Charles Marbles

This was one of my favorite starters among both I loved the cheese feeling there was marble shape balls having schezwan over it the ball was soft and yummy.

4)	Voila Quesidilla

This was a pizza shape tortilla filled with cheese, kimchi, and avocado and heated from the top.

MAINS

5)	Paneer Tikka Masala

Paneer was soft and the taste of the masala was also good it was not much spicy loved this one it was served with butter naan

6)	Naan

The naan was also soft and was freshly made it was loaded with butter and was tasting good with paneer tikka masala

7)	Nasi Goreng Indonesian Style

This was nicely presented the taste of the rice was good it was hot and red in color this was something I tried for the first time.

Coming to the price.

PRICE

DRINKS

1)	Sex On The Beach = Rs355/-

2)	Polish Cooler = Rs450/-

STARTERS

3)	Charles Marbles = Rs425/-

4)	Voila Quesidilla = Rs465/-

MAINS

5)	Paneer Tikka Masala = Rs375/-

6)	Naan =Rs120/-

Excellent place with great service and good food. Had a lovely evening with family. Lots of different varieties and all tasted good. The sizzlers are a must try

This is a very special venue I visited till date.

A venue situated in very top rated area of mumbai.

Breach Candy ,Yess I am talking about Bombay Cartel.This resto bar is very perfectly designed and the space management is been done beautifully and precisely.

The ambiance was perfect and ofcourse the food quality never seems to be compromised.

The staff response was very nice and the orders were on time with perfect recipe and love.

We had plenty of dishes there and we were totally satisfied with the quality we received.

We tried,

DRINKS

1. Peru Ceremolada

A very best in class mocktail served at the place with very little spice of guava and some spicy flavour around the glass.
The glass and the colour it exhibited was nice and appealing for photos .

2.Tusker

That's a cocktail served in very unique glass torred at its base but it looks very impressive and the taste was very nice.
I personally loved this one and will definitely recommend to try this one out anytime.

STARTER

1.Kung Pao Potato

Vegetarians always have plenty of varieties of dishes to try out, just we need to have a proper knowledge of dishes.
We discovered a very special dish here to be a must try one and to feel amaze.

2.Cigar Roll

Done get jumbled with the name though.
To be honest I thought something different but this dish came out on our table and after tasting it really made us feel like in heaven once again.
Fried cigars dipped in schezuan sauce really exhibited impressive taste and looks too.
Served in shots glass made it look even more wonderful.

Then we tried their main courses and those were,

MAIN COURSE

1.TRIPLE SCHEZWAN FRIED RICE

This was very special dish.
Simple looking and also made simple.
Not much spicy and really loved it's simplicity as I like it always
It really made my taste buds go crazy with its smell when we started taking photos.
I would definitely recommend this one.

2.Cheesy Shells Sushi

Personally I never tried this dish but tasting it here changed my mind one side.
This dish is quite an innovative to try here and the ingredients used were made so beautiful the whole dish came out very good looking though it has a unique taste.

Then at last we took desserts in hand.

DESSERTS

1.Deep Fried Oreos

This dessert is very special.The quantity and the quality was so best that we really love this dessert.
Different waffles were put in different dishes and in the middle, molten chocolate was kept.
The looks were very appealing and best in class.

2.Chocolate Fondue

This one is also very recommended dessert.
This place really amazes you with its taste in dessert and all recipes.
I really love the way they represented everything and decoration was first preference.

The staff was courteous and everyone was so good with us that we would love to visit here once again if possible.

Peace

reviews.text: Has a really calm ambience and an extremely rich and beautiful decor. Loved the quality and taste of food. You might want to start with their crunchy “Candy and Green’s House Salad” and end with the most scrumptious “warm chocolate hazelnut cake” which is gluten free And sugar free to make sure you don’t go on guilt trips. On a side note, it is a bit expensive.

Visited this fine restaurant on my birthday for celebrations with bunch of close pals.. They served us the best food too with good service. This restaurant is located at breach candy near peddar road. Restaurant has 2 floors seating arrangement, 4th floor and 5th floor(roof top).

Candy and green is an ideal veg restaurant located in breach candy. They are known for their intercontinental cuisine. I personally enjoyed their house wines and the lotus root sliders.a must visit for the starters and drinks. 
Service: 5/5
Food: 5/5
Ambience: 5/5

I always stop by for lunch here.The bowls are huge, delicious, and well-worth it.

I particularly like Candy & Green because I think the customer service here is AMAZING. 
I first went here with my sister, she’s vegan, very selective about her food quality, freshness, health etc, you get the point.
Since then it’s my go to spot.

They keep having interesting events, 
Pro tip: Check out their rooftop garden where they grow some of their produce, although I’m usually a fan of their wine menu and views up top.
5 Stars, Easy.

Was a very nice meal. I was surprised they didn't have more vegan options. Their pita bread is not vegan, which was surprising. Loved their vegan chocolate cake!

Thai green curry was okay - not as good as most Thai places in the US.

Avocado toast was disappointing.

Service was excellent!

Overall a good experience.

reviews.text: Afzal restaurant is famous for it’s “kepsa rice”.  Kepsa rice is a mixture of chicken fried rice and chicken tandoori. This rice also includes 3-4 boiled eggs along with some salad which includes carrot, onion and tomato. Instead of serving it in a plate or a medium sized utensil, they prefer to serve it in a big thali which gives you the feel of eating like a nawab or a Mughal. The kepsa rice is served in two proportions half and the other one is the full. Half kepsa is ample enough for serving 2-3 people while full on the other hand can easily serve 5 people.  They do have 2 sections ac and non ac. Ac section is located besides the restaurant and goes under the name of Mao Chinese centre.  Talking about the hygiene part, it is below average, so just in case if you’re looking for an hygienic place this is not the right place to be. Instead you can opt for takeaway option which is must better than eating at that particular restaurant. They do serve different types of deserts as well of which caramel custard is the best out of all the deserts served over here.

Recommended by my friend. Ordered triple rice n schezwan rice n chicken hakka noodles. One of the worst noodles I've ever had n both the rice were equally poor in taste. Fried noodles were soft n omelette was the worst prepared. I can get a better one on the roadside. Only saving grace was the boneless lollipop. I swear I won't order or dine here. Not recommended

Delicious food taste always!!!
but due to rush need to be improve fast service   which helps more sales & Profite.
Because this place is good but here are some issues

I have heard of this place from many of my friends that's the reason i had to visit here to have the Kepsa as the name of the outlet says "King of Kepsas". Well thats true the taste you will get here that is unbelievable. We have ordered the Chicken Hydrabadi Kepsa and the taste was mouthwatering. We tried the chicken platter but that was not so value for money.

reviews.text: Cozy ambience. Good music since it was not loud. Can have conversation with friends. Very good experience. Nice beer options. Liked the German one.

Quite happening place in Belapur. Ambience and the interiors are quite appealing. Talking about food the taste is nice. We really loved the Pizza and nachos.
Sometimes there is live music going on which just sets the good mood. Love this place!
Food-4/5
Staff-5/5
Ambience-5/5

It is inside a small shady Bhoomi mall with no parking. 
Went for a birthday. 
Got a table with a nice window and a nice view. 
The place is extremely beautiful on the inside. Loved the interiors. 

We asked them to reduce the volume as were seated right under the speakers and couldn’t hear each other at all but that didn’t go through at all. It was a Saturday night so the place was bustling with people so the volume never went down.
There was only 1 server/waiter for quite a few tables so we struggled a little with that. So service was slightly slow too. 
However the food made up for it. The food was great. 
We asked them to play Happy Birthday when they brought the cake but that didn’t happen either. So had a happy-sad experience there.
Good place for having a beer with friends even punjabi food is delicious one should must try it .

Came here for an office party and it certainly is a great place for the overall ambience it provides. The food is also quite good. A good place for both a small group as well as large one. 

Ambience: (4/5)
Opens out into a large opens space and there is a separate section available to the right after entry. There is a small stage that is there and a DJ section to the left after entering near the bar. There are limited toilets so when it’s a larger crowd this is something to be mindful about. There are many interesting design elements that make up the space. Some brilliant wall decor and lighting. 

Food: (4/5)
The buffet menu was extremely good. I was especially surprised by the quality of the fried rice. It had a really great flavour and just get light. The other dishes were also great, but nothing compared to the friend rice. The cake for dessert was also quite good, not too sweet, but still rich in flavour. 

Summary: (4/5)
Good place in Belapur to drop by with friends or office colleagues. It’s not too expensive and hence make for a good even especially if there is drinking involved. Do drop by and enjoy a good evening here.

reviews.text: Was an amazing seven day experience.  Staff was very friendly and they were accurate and made sure we stayed safe during this stay.

I stayed this hotel for business and every single staff are so helpful and friendly in professional manner.  Close to airport and hotel is beautiful. Room is very clean and amenity is perfect, a lot of bottle of water is placed in room.
 Afreen gave us a lovely memorable gifts was such a kind gesture and I was so touched. Thank you for your hospitality I will come back end of this month again. see you soon.

Definitely recommend this hotel.
I have stayed while being quarantined, facility is good, rooms are spacious, staff is good, but do have issues with quality of food. On an average of 5, I will give 3.
Poor service, anything you ask for is either not available or it will take minimum 30 minutes to show, food is way too pricey like for a simple soup it’s 695, staff are way too rude

Our Company made us stay in this hotel for quarantine...First of all, after hearing JW Marriott, I thought it would be of great experience..But in reality,it's quite opposite..
1.Bed was too small,even after repeated requests,room was not changed.
2.Everyday they r bringing breakfast after 9am,lunch after 1400hrs,which is not right time to have either breakfast or lunch..This has been pointed out and they say they're helpless.
3.Requested yoga mat and books to read,which they couldn't provide.Atleast during quarantine,they need to provide yoga mats.
4.Everyday need to ask green tea bags as they are providing only 2 per day.How cheap.Why can't they provide for whole duration of stay.

reviews.text: The staff was very amicable and served quickly. I've always been able to get a seat for 2+ people. Its got some really good chicken risotto and chocolate fondue. My review on dama dum mast kalandar (chembur)

It’s a authentic sindhi cuisine restaurant. At a very convenient location to reach right on the highway in chembur. In two floors ground a fine dine and the first floor a lounge like setup with swings and all both the floor are very spacious and very well made up. The décor is too good with small artifact and paintings on walls.

We had

For drinks 

Whiskey Sour (must try)

Muddled boondi mojito (must try)

Balam kesariya

Blind date 

For food 

Aloo tuk

Tariyal teevan chaap (must try)

Methi zinga tandoori

Sindhi gold chicken tikka

Keema JA Bhalla

Sindhi Tikki

Sindhi kadhi with pav 

And the last a nice roasted papad with four different types of chutneys (sindhi cuisine in incomplete without a padad)

The food and staff is good and must try place..

Awesome interiors , lovely staff and great food sums up Duma Dum Mast Kalandar .if you are looking for some awesome lip smacking sindhi food this is the place to visit .KURKURE CHANA , Sindhi kadhi are not to be missed
Descent restaurant with good interiors. Food is also delicious . Staffs are polite and the service is great.

Duma Dum mast Kalander is one of the finest Restaurant in Chembur known for the desi styled old Sindi Food.
This is best place for spend your valuable time with your friends, family.

Ambiance of this place is attractive. This place beautifully and we'll decorated with paper fans on wall, wall painting, lights. Ambiance of this place is specious.

Seating arrangement of this place is very well organised and managed in respect of couples, group of friends and families and couples.
They have attractive combination of table , chair and sofas which give great look to this place.

Duma Dum Mast Kalander staff is very polite and professional and services given by them were fast . They helped us to choose delicious dish during the visit.

Talking about food ...
They serves delicious and authentic Sindi food which really tasted so delicious.

We've Tried Here:
#Mocktails:
✓ Traditional Sindi Cool Drink :
It was a watermelon based Drink which was mixture of watermelon syrup, mint. This drinks was very refreshing. Love this Drink.. Recommended.

✓Thadal:
This drinks was awesome. Definitely Go for this drink. Highly Recommended

#Staters:
✓Lahori Chicken Tikka:
This was one of best tikka I tasted ever. Perfectly made with spices. Highly Recommended

✓Bheja Fry with Tandoori Pav:
This dish was superb. The bheja fry masala tasted so delicious. Must Try it..

✓ Tarial Macchi (Pomfret):
This was fried pomfret fish which perfectly marinated with spices. Personally I liked Tarial Macchi so much.

#Main Course:
✓Sindhi Chicken Biryani:
Liked the Sindhi chicken biryani. Biryani which had a Sindhi flavour touch. Delicious and so Yummy.

#Dessert:
✓ Khoya Gulab Jamun:
Gulab Jamun was superb. This Dessert never disappointed you anywhere.

✓Kulfi

Overall my experience at Duma Dum Mast kalander was great. Liked the food, service and ambience. Great Place!!!

reviews.text: This is the best pizza place in the bay! I’d love to visit the place again. You can go with your friends, family, partner or whosoever you wish to.
Pizza is tasteless and far too dry. And too expensive for its quality
Beautiful place. Delicious food. Rate is quite high. Good location. 10 min walking distance from Church Gate rail station. Sophisticated area. Beside marine line.

Started with a delicious cup of coffee with helped me cope with all the air sickness from the flight.
I had Veg exotic pizza and Caesar salad. Both were equally good. 
The pizza was the best I had in a long long time. Regular pizza, not even thin crust and yet so good

Ended with a soothing cold coffee. Very glad. :)

5/5 for everything.
Would surely love to visit again ❤️

A very good hangout place for all types of crowd....
They have nice variety of craft beers....
Great location.....
Amazing ambience....
The service is above average.....
Food just above average.....
Quite costly....
Valet parking available....
Must try in Colaba....!
I would love to visit again....!

This place is well located. We were greeted well by the staff at the entrance, overall the staff was very friendly and courteous. Service was excellent and quick. Dishes which we ordered were also very good. Overall we had a great experience.
Amazing beer (try the Peach-Ginger one!) & super friendly and helpfull staff. The food, although we did not try, looked really good too. I‘ll be back for sure.

restaurants.address: Minoo Manor Building, 7, Captain Prakash Pethe Marg, Badhwar Park, Apollo Bandar, Cuffe Parade, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400005, India

reviews.text: SO YUMMY! Beautiful decor and lovely ambiance. All the dishes were tasty and really elegantly presented. I especially loved the Yemeni Mandi which was lightly smoked and had incredible flavor. Especially the rice had a perfect smoky flavor and the lamb was a tender accompaniment. The rich baklava we shared for dessert was a wonderful end to the meal, sprinkled with the shattered petals of a nitrogen-frozen rose!

It was my wife's birthday. We wanted to go out and try some different cuisine and after very long search on #zomato and #google we found this place. Decision to go at this place was the best cause the food was best. Person who was suggesting the menu was very helpful and knowledgeable. We ordered as per his recommendation veg & non veg both ...it turned out so good. Little expensive but it was with great food service and quality. Must visit place if you like to explore your taste buds..

It was a great lunch in Bayroute Powai.
I had been their with my friends and as expected the food was fantastic up to the mark.
What i liked here was their signature dish bayroute hummus.
It was really tempting and mouth watering.
The ambience gives a royal feeling.
The waiters are very friendly and gave good service.
The drinks named as reyhan,rose melting juice are one of the special juices of the restaurant.
All over the experience was good.
Would love to recommend all to visit once in your life time with your family and friends.

We went to this place after reading a lot of reviews,the place is very finely done and gives a very Turkish feel.
The attendants are very welcoming,menu is exhausting and portion is decent.
There is a lot to try from the menu so I would suggest go in a big group.
Good job guys🤘

Truly loved the food here. Once you get through the daunting menu and finally make some choices, it seems you can’t go wrong. I read some reviews about the demeanor of the staff here — some of it seems true. But who cares. They do their job and you get one of the best meals you may ever have. We went back again and would go again if still in Mumbai.

restaurants.Features: All-Day Dining, Great Buffets, Best food
restaurants.address: Shop No:7, Ground Floor, The Arcade Building, Gate 2 World Trade Centre Colaba, Ganesh Murti Nagar, Cuffe Parade, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400005, India

reviews.text:
Visited for dinner on a Saturday evening. They had a teenager's birthday party going on. It was fairly noisy when we entered but the lady at the restaurant brought down the volume within minutes. Really appreciated!
The pan fried noodles were crispy and soft in the right measure and had lots of chicken and vegetables. The khao suey had a good amount of gravy and was full of flavour. An enjoyable dinner experience

I had a visit for a private event and found the venue and the location pretty good. Talking about the staff, they were humble and down to earth and ready to go a step forward just to help you. Well talking about the food, I'm sure you won't be dissatisfied.

Super chic place. Flamboyante was under renovation when I went but Hammer and song were also hosting the flamboyante menu. The place is super cosy. The music was good and to optimum level where you can talk to people around. The menu is limited and the food is very tasty. They have clean washrooms.

A perfect fine dine restaurant in a very quite and nice place. The food rates are above average but the service sets its own benchmark. the quality and taste of the food is really good. But you do have to wait for your order to be placed.

Awesome Ambience, very tasty food, great staff and a quite spacious restaurant. We tried Khowsey and four seasons with Asparagus. Both were good. The hotel owner/manager was also very warm. They made a point to make us feel comfortable at every point. As it was my birthday, they also arranged for a special dessert along with birthday music as you can see in the images.

reviews.text:
Hi guys if you are in dadar and looking for one of the best place to have Veg or NonVeg food or drinks 

Then this is one of the best place to visit... 

This place is simply amazing for having food with family and friends ..They have a good ambiance and they offer variety of tasty veg /non veg  food and hard & soft drink..
You will simply love the taste of food.

Must visit...
Good place to visit near to dadar station east side. It serves delicious food with good quantity. Staff is very friendly do visit and have some good food alongwith some booze🍻

Ambiance is very good. Try Mojito and chicken tandoori when you visit here.

Also the Live music was very entertaining. Nice place to hangout with your friend. 

They only need to improve the speed of serving. Waiting for food and drinks irritates when you are hungry.
Its such a lovely place...nice staff.. Serving yummy food with smile.will surely be back with my frens
Good food. Slow service. Call for the bill in advance as they take 10 mins.

restaurants.address: Dharamputra Pritam Estate, Dr Baba Saheb Ambedkar Rd, Lokmanya Tilak Colony, Dadar, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400014, India

reviews.text: This place is located besides Dadar station, due to which it is easily accessible for all the college students as well as for the corporate people. Pretty good place to spend time with your loved ones as the ambience is pretty good accompanied by lip smacking food and cheap booze. Cocktails, nachos and pizzas are highly recommended.

As the name suggests, its really a place you can visit multiple times and you wont be disappointed..
To start with happy hours, they have happy hours from 6-9 pm where you get really cheap alcohol..
Their Nachos are pretty famous, one can also look into ordering fries and pizzas to eat.. 
Plus the dance floor. Saturday night all you wanna do is dance !!

Mrp is located in Dadar. 
Ambiance is nice. 
The food is good and tasty. They have happy hours from 6pm to 9pm for alcohol at a good price. 
Saturday nights after 9pm you will hardly get place to sit mostly bar area so make sure you are there earlier. The music is good and mostly on weekends they have live music.

The ambiance is beautiful. Food quality was upto the level that you would expect in short scrumptious. Down side for us was DJ. We thought we would get to dance on the beats but no it did not go that well. Overall it was a good place to enjoy a get-together with your friends.

Very very young vibe..... Great bar games on each table.... Perfect for college / young earners type place. Value for money drink options....happy hours are a good spread esp for groups. Good music.... Though can be a bit loud. Parking is not possible. Not at all Kid friendly. Convenient for late evening drink sessions with train station nearby. Perfect if you want to catch a drink before heading to Pune by Bus 😉

restaurants.address: 1, Swami Ganjivandas Marg, Dadar East, Dadar, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400014, India

reviews.text: This placehplace proper hygiene and social distancing policies in place for current pandemic situations. Many shops have opened up and offer almost everything one may require. The restaurants are providing both take away and delivery options.

Great food. Great ambiance. Great vibes.
It is a place with typical Dhaba feel in the middle of the town, both in ambiance and in food as well.
Has a good number of varities in dishes, I had tried veg food.. tasted great.
Found it a bit costly, approx 1200 pp but it is worth it.
Food is good. Not at all economic. Service is good but slow. The restaurant charges service tax in the bill. Look out if u do not wish to pay the same. Ps note that u can deny paying service tax

Best tandoori experience of my life. I remember going to the Dhaba as a child as the owners son was my class mate.  The air is filled with the fragrance of tandoori chicken and the taste is a heavenly experience. Truly one for the bucket list. Thank you Kohli family for your legacy!

It's a hotel with restaurant. A++ for the interior and you will get all the cuisines available. On 31st dec they charge extra and rates are lil expensive as per the other restaurants but food quality is worth the penny.

restaurants.address: 68, Kiran Building, Ranade Rd, Dadar West, Shivaji Park, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400028, India

reviews.text: Being originally from Dadar, I was surprised I didn't know of this place, till a friend suggested it for getting cake for my parents. But after having their cakes and bakery products, I am extremely happy and would recommend this place to all my friends and family. Of all the cakes I have had, I would really recommend Oven Fresh Dutch Truffle cake! It's really divine and feel like having it daily. I also loved their croissants and blueberry danish. Overall, an excellent place!

Ovenfresh is one of its kind of bakery cum restaurant. They bake their own cakes and each of the cake is so unique in taste! It's just mouth watering. I personally love their blueberry cheese cake. It's a must try if you go there. Also try there sizzlers. I used to love apple cider here but they stopped serving it long long back. Really miss that.
Cheater, my order was placed and not delivered. No one even answers mobile and landline numbers. This is fake company of thieves . Please do not waste your money ordering cake from oven fresh online.

This place has been perennially popular with Shivaji Park folks. Its range of vegetarian casual Continental fare has many takers. The sandwiches and sizzlers are pretty popular as are the Mexican nachos, tacos and enchiladas. The dessert counter is usually crowded and its indulgent chocolate cakes get many takers.It is difficult to get a table here during lunch time so be prepared to wait.

The sizzlers are pretty popular here and the place becomes a tad smoky during rush hour

The best consistent food place I have been to and keep going back to 
Mexican, Italian, sizzlers, desserts, cakes, soups -😍😀😊👍🏻👌🏻👌🏻 all extra ordinary. 
No table booking , long queue expected after 6.45-7pm for dinner!
Parking is a bit of a challenge, narrow roads. But all worth.

restaurants.Cuisines: American, Fast Food, Italian, Burger, Salad, Healthy Food
restaurants.address: Meher Premises, Shivaji Park, Dadar West, Dadar, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400028, India

reviews.text: Best cheese cake in whole Mumbai 😋.. Awesome ambience. Bakery products Recommended.

"Home Chef All Day Dining" in Dadar, Mumbai. I recently visited this place and I liked the peaceful ambience. It had a decent staff and hygienic atmosphere. The pastries were tempting, mains were tasty as well and the starters were wonderfully delicious. It's a place where you want to visit again and over again.

They sell stale food stuffs. Shout at customers if you complain. We purchased a cake on Sunday (26th July) evening and it was stinking chemical. When we complained, the answer we get is that other customers have not complained. Most of the bread and other products are old as well (i was planing to buy and checked the dates). Take your own risk when you order food from here. They don't follow any social distancing and neither check customers for temp.  For your own safety and health, avoid the place. The lady sitting in the counter is most rude one I have ever met in this business. Huge health hazard. Kitchen is very dirty if you get a chance to peen from the next door or from cash counter.

Home Chef is a the finest dining located in Shivaji Park Dadar area.
The ambience of the place is very simple and beautiful.
They have a huge variations in their mocktails and also they customise it according to the way you need.

The freshness of the food and the ingredients they use will make you to come over here again and again
The Chicken and Chinese menu is also too good.
Also will recommend for pizza and pasta they serve here as they are cheese loaded with thin crisp base.
Overall a great experience ❤
Would definitely love to visit again
Tried the nachos here which were satisfactory. They can be better at both taste and quality. The chocolate mouse was good, worth a try. The ambience was good and the staff was friendly too.

restaurants.Features: Food Hygiene Rated Restaurants In Mumbai, Best of Mumbai
restaurants.address: 2nd Floor, Nakshatra Mall, Ranade Rd, Dadar West, Dadar, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400028, India

reviews.text: Great service good staff. For was very good we had ordered veg as well as non veg food. Everything was great. Will come here again.. The beverage and the service was very good.

I went to angrezi dhaba @ dadar some couples of months ago 
I tried couple of dishes of there i started from mocktail to main course 

1️⃣:- firstly i tried mocktails and juices 🥤 u can gulp it in between your meals or with dessert too.
u can try their freashly fruit juices its really exotic. Very attractive moktail for pictures clicking. Balance sweetness & was perfectly prepared.

2️⃣-Next i tried garlic bread there were 4 pieces in a plate and garlic bread was too tasty n soft the size of the bread was quiet large but they don provide u any sauses or chutney with it. As the taste is little different so you can enjoy without chutney or any sauces

3️⃣:-Then i tried chiken platter it was very very mouth watering cheese 🧀 was topped over it  platter was garnished with some carrot and cabbage also a bowl of green chutney the chiken was very soft and marinated with garlic 🧄 ginger paste along with some spices in it we luved it i would like to rate 10 out 10 to this chiken platter

4️⃣- And the last i ordered chicken crispy tempting 🤩🤑 and this chicken crispy was garnished with coriander . I like the taste was not so spicy u can have it some szhewan sause as per your taste or its a good option to start your dinner 🥘

➡️Ambience-  It's  an Indo-western fusion restaurant and bar.They have an outside seating as well as well-decorated dim indoor ambience with full of load music with attracts so much.
one of those places which has a really quirky ambience and a unique way of serving food.

Ambience-5/5
Service-5/5
Taste-5/5
worth for money-5/5
Nice ambiance... delicious food... but take more time to prepare order and expensive

Awesome place for dinner. Very nice ambiance. Delicious food. It's located at dadar west and also nearby railway station so it's easy for everyone to reach here easily. You Will enjoy partying here if you are going with family.

Though this place looks odd from outside , it’s for sure a gem . We were surprised to find a very small AC space inside the restaurant. When we asked for a better space the captain showed us a huge outdoor seating . It was wow by all aspect . The ambience was great , topped with decent service . Overall a great place if you want to spend some time with your friends . The food is decent as well.

restaurants.Cuisines: Maharashtrian, South Indian, Street Food, Desserts, Mithai
restaurants.address: 4, Sanskruti, Gadkari Chauk, Lady Jamshedji Rd, opp. Shiv Sena Bhavan, Dadar West, Dadar, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400028, India

reviews.text: There is no better place than Aaswad for Maharashtrian cuisine. Authentic Zhunka and Puran poli, If you’re lucky then try Modak without fail, things is most of the time they run out of Modak  very fast. If you like pure “Loni” on top of your Thalipeeth, this is the place with spicy “thecha” and “Loni”, ohh its flavorsome. Full of happiness,when we visit we order at lease 6-7 items. There is always a wait time but they have new renovated spot,post Metro development, with plenty space. If you go for Siddhivinayak temple darshan, instead of eating nearby restaurants, try Aaswad, for authentic Maharashtrian taste.

My all time favourite place for typical Maharashtrian food.
Ambience is good with pretty interiors.
Staff is super friendly and courteous.

Some must try dishes are puran poli ice-cream, pitale bhakar, caramel custard, cheese masala pav ,piyush, vada pav. 

They have come up with a diet thali which is super delicious.
Prices are pocket friendly too.

Definitely a must visit place for Maharashtrian food lovers.

The service here is really great and appreciable. The Cost of all items are affordable and not as high as the facilities and amenities that they are providing. The taste here is truly great and totally worth it. All the food items are very tasty and hygienic. And quantity is also satisfactory.
It was a great experience to visit here.
All the food items v had were delicious. Had a soulful meal. Authentic maharashtrian cuisine. A must try.
Great place to have a taste of the Marathi delicacies. Cozy place. Well managed and hospitable. Happy hogging!

restaurants.address: Thakur Mall, near Dahisar Check Naka, Ketkipada, Dahisar East, Mira Bhayandar, Maharashtra 401107, India

reviews.text: Superb place to hang out with your friends and family. I love the food. And ambiance. Specially Nachos. Please try nachos at TBC

Recently visited The Boat Club which is in Thakur Mall (Dahisar). 
This place has a cool ambience and comfortable sitting area. 
Food here tasted good but would  recommend it to be much better. Overall it was a great experience visiting this place.

TBC is a great place to spend a weekend afternoon or evening, cozily sipping a drink or enjoying some great options off their menu with a large group or small. The staff are courteous and friendly and the food and drinks are great! We were served by Faruk and he was friendly and ensured we had a comfortable afternoon! Head on over to TBC!

Located inside Thakur Mall, the place is big and has comfortable seating. The staff is well mannered and their service is quick. Their menu has a wide variety of options to choose from.

We had the following :

▪️Crispy Chicken - Crispy pieces of Chicken that were delicious. Tender on the inside, they were perfect in terms of texture.

▪️Barbeque Chicken Pizza - Sweet chunks of Chicken as topping on a uniquely shaped Pizza base. Cheese was scrumptious..😋

▪️Stuffed Chicken Breast Sizzler - Stuffed Chicken was the highlight of this dish. Delectable and the juicy Chicken had a very flavoursome stuffing. The veggies on the side were nicely cooked and the Mashed potato creamy..😍

reviews.author_name: S E N T I N E L
reviews.text: A very nice restaurant located in the heart of Thakur mall Dahisar. The space is very big were you can enjoy dancing also can have a big gathering. The interior is also good. They have two separate areas one for food and one for lounge even they have separate bar area. The music was little bit low. The service provide by staff was also good. The we have ordered both veg and non veg dishes. My best dishes was the chicken lagasne. We enjoy here a lot. Price is little bit high but you will get both quality and quantity. Recommended to everyone thank you. ❤️

reviews.text: Good atmosphere... Family section available.. Both AC & non AC restaurant.. Mainly parking available for bike & car..  Amazing tasty 😋 food... Smoking zone available... Location is good.. Highly recommend.. Veg & non veg food available as per our requirements.. Take away facility is there..  Must visit

Beware !!
Ordered Mutton Biryani yesterday 06th Sep, the mutton tasted a little funky & bland !! Had to throw away a box of biryani, confirmed next day with a stomach upset. Never experienced bad food from BBC, this one was unacceptable. Never again ordering food from them, at least not till the next year. Stay Safe.
I was only standing outside. Still you guys are asking for review!!

Borivali biriyani centre is a heaven for the biriyani lovers...Every items here is unique and delicious.....some of the must try items here are:-
1.Continental sizzler
2.Pav bhaji fondue
3.Ciger rolls
4.Chocolate brownie
5.Blue lagoon 
6.Chicken Tikka biriyani
All the above items are awesome and you can even try new more items to discover more tasty meals
The ambience and the food is good. The customer service is also decent. There's usually a waiting on weekends but there's a big waiting area to accommodate big crowds. All in all - 5 stars

reviews.text: Niche category hotel serving global and Indian cuisine in a menu mix format. The portion size is too small. So if you're a foodie, you might still be left with hunger pangs. Otherwise, service is great! Staff is friendly and helpful. Food is also tasty!

Mondo fine dine is a place especially for romantic dates or candle light dinner.
Service and ambience here is great.
They have a 6 course meal option with different set menu from around world to choose from.
We option for Mexican food and harayana chicken.

❌Cons
1.sitting arrangement is less
2.food quantity is less
3.Quite Expensive

Good place. Went for set meal. Friendly staff. Good place to celebrate special occasion.
Ambiance : Not very specious but good enough to sit at ease. Dim lights no music promotes more on conversation.
Food : It was good but Not something which can make me come again. Great presentation can improve more for indian taste. 
Overall good experience. +1 for the staff.
Very nice Restaurant, Have been with friends and enjoyed there food their ambience and of-course services they offers.

Finally ticked the Box after a couple of positive reviews and recommendation to try out this place that serves good Gourmet Food.

Unique Concept! Great Good! Just the right Portions! Decent Ambience! Value for Money! Thank you Vishal n Mac for the hospitality.. Keep up the good work Team Mondo :)

Surely coming back for the next Cuisine/Menu change.. 👍

restaurants.address: Gagangiri Complex, Kandarpada Rd, Shiva Shakti Nagar, Kandarpada, Dahisar West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400068, India

reviews.text: I ❤ havmor ice cream well maintained  customer service is also good my all time favorite

A great family restaurant to visit. Awesome service and the food also tasted very good. Definitely try the Chef's Special Dishes and their blueberry Cheesecake , they are just too good. They even have a lounge and a banquet hall above the restaurant.

A great place to go with family and friends. Honey mustard chicken, majestic chicken, chicken rara were some of the dishes I tried and they were just over the top. Also tried some mocktails (pink lady, kiwi cooler) and desserts (blueberry cheese cake, caramel custard) which was a perfect ending to our dinner.
Good for boozing. Too loud music. Service pretty slow. However food is tasty. Need to wait for good food.

Royal master chef finedine and banquet.

It is a continental, northindian, asian cusine.

It is located Anand Park, Dahisar West, Mumbai.

They have amazing ambience with fabulous interior Decor. They have good music system.

I have visited here with my friend. Their staff was very polite to us. 

Loved their quick table service.

I have ordered,

Rose cooler🍷
It was a good refreshing drink, which was presented in a very good way. 

Dakshini Murg (Chef's Special)
Comes with a six pieces of chunks of chicken. It is like a southindian starter.  Prepared very well.

Subz Gunchao (RECOMMENDED)
It is a mix vegetables northindian gravy. The taste was very delicious and excellent. Must try this with butter roti.

Chocolate flourless🥧
It taste like a sizzle brownie. And very sweet and delicious taste it has. Good dessert to end up with your meal.

All over experience with Masterchef FineDine And Banquets was outstanding.

Thanks

Very nice place to hangout. Good ambiance and DJ music. The Lounge bar serves good snacks and food that are very tasty and admirable. The staff though in rush would act stupid and you may find delays if getting your food served.

X sky lounge bar is now office known as Trap Lounge..... It's an awesome place to hangout with your friends and loved ones..... The sitting arrangements... The ambiance everything is perfect.... Food quality n quantity both r nice..... Do visit this place.
Great place to hangout with friends and family. Nice Ambience.Live music is also good.
Really liked the food and the ambience. We were very early so it was pretty much empty. Could click some nice pictures and enjoy the sunset. Would recommend atleast going once

reviews.text: I just love that place. Good ambiance, great service, and pleasant lighting both at day time and night time. Awesome place to sit and do your work. Power connections are available for laptops and mobile phone making it an ideal place for official meetings in Dombivili.
We tried soupy masala noodles, garlic bread with cheese and our all time fav devil's own. Noodles were spicy and yummm. Garlic bread was good. Devil's own al always soo refreshing

Very well maintained with ample of space. good for short meetups. the ambience is calm with good songs on their playlist. The devil's own with vanilla ice-cream is a must try. Smoked chicken sandwich is good snack to try on. vanilla latte is also something you can try out apart from the regular latte available on the menu.

Slightly disappointed!!! Good Ambience though! Located on a famous street in Dombivli. Usually not crowded but recently it has gathered attention. I happened to buy a flavored water.. But even though it was available they refused to sell it.  This has happened to me earlier too with some other items on the menu! Good to hang out but!
Best frappe I ever had. Nive ambience and humble staff.

restaurants.address: Shiv Sagar CHS, Shop No, 8, Mahatma Phule Rd, opp. IDBI Bank, Vishnu Nagar, Dombivli West, Dombivli, Maharashtra 421202, India

reviews.text:
It's a good place with station nearby location for better service. Currently in corona times, it's serving take out and delivery only. Prices are a bit on higher side but not too costly.

Have ordered food from them many times and now ordered pahadi kabab. Taste was good and quantity was decent (8 pieces). Do try their soup it's good tasting. Biryani is also a good to go

Overall rating 3.5-4 because of quantity to price ratio.
Hygienic Place and Good Food taste
Nice place to hangout with friends and family.
Okaish restaurant with decent price for the food order veg triple rice 1 by 2 and the quantity was surprisingly good, Taste was as usual and their schezwan chutney was nice.

Located near dombivili station..opens at 11 in morning till midnight.

Available on Zomato and swiggy so you can order right from your home easily

For dine out you get ac and non ac room...with good customer service no doubt

From menu you have alot from Chinese also Indian dishes. Tandoors are mouth watering. Not to worry as it is pocket friendly

Rush hours for dine out on sundays so plan accordingly before visiting.

I most prefer for home delivery.

reviews.text: Best non-vegetarian food .

I had Chicken Sukka and Tandul Bhakri. Both were tasty,. Chicken Sukka was neither too oily or too spicy. Served with a piece of lemon and onion.

The outlet has limited seating space, decent decor, more suited for take away than sit-in dining.
Best place for Malvani food, specialy nonveg
nice place.. must try dish : Prawns biryani..😍👍
Lovely homely food. Local flavors. Tasty non-vegetarian. Go for fish thali. Worth it
