reviews.text:
Nice ambience.
Great variety of food thanks to so many restaurants/ stalls. The food was fine, not so amazing. Some restaurants had amazing variety and dishes. Would have really loved to have more dessert options and also food from Socials.
But overall a great place to hang out.

This place has such an amazing ambience with a lush green vertical garden on the inside. They have amazing options in food. I loved the place. My friends and I spent a good amount of time in there since we had reached early at 6 pm. You must check out this place.

A very lively atmosphere, this place has a menu with multiple varieties available! Tried a cocktail called Thai Maalish. Would not recommend it. The nachos are good! They also serve Jain food on request. The interiors are really good and give it a festive vibe.

A food court kind of a set up makes it a really nice place to hangout. You have loads of options to choose from, various cuisines to try out. The fact that you can order a variety of small dishes from different places really appeals to some. The ambience is super cool. Recently they have added table service for which you will be charged in the bill but it makes things a lot easier now. Occasionally they do project sports on the screen. A nice place to visit if you find yourself in Kamla mills and can't figure out what you wanna eat. Come here and try a little of everything!

Concept of the restaurant is quite clear: Flea Bazaar of Food from around the world and India, and the decor manages to.communicate the same. 

But as far as putting that concept into action is when it goes either wrong or right....

For Flea Bazaar it goes quite wrong. Half of the things on the menu weren't available. And out of the limited choice we had to choose from, nothing quite interesting. 

Music was good and whatever we ordered on the plate was decent enough but not up to the standards one would think of. 

In all, a decent place to catch up with friends.

restaurants.address: Flea Bazaar Café, Unit No 5, 1st Floor, Trade View Building, Oasis City Complex, Lower Parel, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400013, India

reviews.text:
Del Italia is a part of the Flea Bazar Cafe. They sell two things; Pasta and Pizza. 

We went for the Vegetarian Pizza called the Smoked Vegetable Provençal Pizza! It had fresh toppings and cheese was cheeeeeeeesy, you can see it for yourself in the pictures! 

They also serve you a side of melted garlic butter so that you can eat the pizza crust by dipping in it. I have never seen any other pizza joint taking care of the waste pizza crust issue without charging you an additional fee.
Good ambience... Music... Food... Good place to go with your friends

Really good pastas and pizzas 
Loved the pesto pasta and the carbonara ! 
Super reasonable and yummy!
Its nice ambience of specific this place was nice price is also resonable overall its a good hangout place
It is good place plzz visit once. I loved the service and quality of food was also good

restaurants.address: Elphinstone Building, Horniman Circle, Veer Nariman Road, Kala Ghoda, Fort, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400001, India

reviews.text: Always a great place to be at, the vibe and service is excellent. Now post lockdown, there are markers on the floor to enable social distancing while placing orders and collecting them for take-away.

Starbucks fort branch is my all-time favorite. It is quite spacious as compared to other branches. The food quality is much better than other branches. The atmosphere is very good and everything is well maintained.

Located at Horniman Circle, this is a rather quite place for a pit stop and have a sip of some mesmerizing Starbucks coffees and some refreshing snacks. The prices usually ranges from INR 250+ for coffees, depending on what your preferences are. The place is comfortable to spend some time with friends or loved ones. The staff is extremely helpful and friendly.
Amazing copy. Fantastic ambience and awesome music. What more one could as for...

One of the Beautiful Starbucks Outlet in town.. so Nicely maintained. Place is really huge with lots of seating arrangements. Place is also very spacious.
They sell some of the yummiest coffee's here.
They also sell coffee beans, sippers, mugs, bottles and much more..
You can always fulfill your taste buds here

restaurants.address: 140, Ground Floor, Commerce house, Nagindas Master Road, Kala Ghoda,, Fort, near Ayubs, Kala Ghoda, Fort, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400001, India

reviews.text:
99 pancakes which is located in many places but i have visited fort outlet has it is near from my friend's home, as i have visited their. So after a long time decided to visit here to have a new flavours of desserts from here.

They have good Ambience. Also their interior decor was very well and they have good numbers of sitting arrangements.

They have installed good music system. 

I have ordered,

Exotica Pizza 
It is a regular size of pizza which costs around 130 with tax. The taste of the pizza was superb and the base was thin and properly cooked.

Dark and white chocolate pancake.
Comes with 6pcs of Mini pancakes with a chocolate loaded cream and with black and white choco chips toppings.

They have quick and fast service. Loved the staff behaviour and the way they have presented the desserts was excellent and worth.

They have taken all the safety measures. Staff were worn mask, gloves and head cover cap. 

They have parking for bikes and one car. They have only indoor sittings.

All over experience with 99 pancakes was superb and wonderful. 

Thanks for a amazing service.

Enjoyed ordering food from this dessert store.

I would recommend trying their waffle as they are soft as cotton, just the way I like them.

In the pancakes, they have a wide range of toppings, my personal favourite is the salted caramel and cream & jelly.

In Savouries they have very good pizzas, freshly made and served.

While eating you can see that the batter they use for each of these items is freshly made as it reflects on the food

Waffles and pancakes are mine all time favourite and during this time I missed them a lot, but all thanks to 99pancakes that they are up with their outlets.

Chocolate heaven waffle and KitKat waffle is what I love the most of this place they are amazing and I prefer them a lot, also the Paneer pizza is good with a crunchy base.

Also they are taking proper precautions and maintaining the social distance which is the most important thing. I am waiting to order soon again.

99 pancakes is the best place to have pancakes.
If you are looking to binge on pancakes and you are unsure where to head for some yummy ones 99 pancakes should be. 
A box full of hot pancakes with Nutella overload is true love. 
Each pancake i ordered was different from another, standing out with its unique taste. 
Valentine pancake was also so nice and yummy Nutella and whipped cream pancakes which turned out to be amazing in taste.

Absolutely Delicious pancakes and crepes. Tried the chocolate indulgence and it came in 6 small pancakes drizzled with crunchies and chocolate syrup that was just finger licking good.
Would definitely recommend 99 pancakes if you are craving a dessert delight!
The pizza was a good add on and they have quite a variety of unique dishes.
Waiting to try it out again.

restaurants.address: Sector 15, Ghansoli, Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra 400701, India

reviews.text:
Points ,
1) try Gobhi Paratha, still if you don't like Flower it's amazing
2) Try Ghee Dal Tadka It's nice
3) most of the parathas are tasty

Not five star only because of the ambiance they provide is not catchy and decorative. You can visit here for taste for sure. Best paratha I ever tasted in Mumbai.

A must visit place for everyone who is in love with home made Parathas. A small yet a cozy place for your taste buds to relish on the stuffed aloo Parathas, paneer Parathas , sattu Parathas and what not. The green chutney they serve along with the Parathas is just too fabulous for the tongue. The place has line of healthy fruit juices and milkshakes at to appetize your thirst. I tried alu  paratha good taste

restaurants.address: 4, Charu Patil Marg, Sector 3, Ghansoli, Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra 400701, India

reviews.text:
Ambience- 4/5
Service- 5/5
Food- 4.5/5
Pocket Friendly - 4.5/5
Overall - 4.5/5

Navratree Prasad is a vegetarian Fine Dine restaurant in Ghansoli.
This place can be easily sighted from outside Ghansoli Station.

Talking about the ambience, this place is thoughtfully designed to give simple yet spacious seating arrangements.  One of the wall that is covered with plates and bowls, looks impressive.

Being a weekday, the footfall was moderate, so fortunately we received a wonderful hospitality. They have ample staff to handle big numbers on any given day. For food we totally relied on our table captain. Right from the juices till the desserts, we loved almost everything we had.

Lets come to food now:
Off the mark, we started with juices. Ordered for Cocktail, Orange and Watermelon. All these were amazingly refreshing, but I would recommend Cocktail juice if one would like to have tangy and sweet taste. Also tried Sweet Lassi and Kesar Lassi, Sweet Lassi was yum and thick.

Next we headed to their soup section,
We ordered for Palak soup, Sweet corn soup and Manchow soup. Here, according to me, sweet corn and Manchow soup was nothing different from what we usually have at different places, but if you are a spinach lover, then definitely try creamy spinach soup.

Coming to the starters:
Here comes Paneer Koliwada, Spicy chilly Manchurian dry, Corn Palak Kebab, Mushroom Tikka and hara bhara kebab.
Spicy Chilly manchurian tasted well, the presentation was good, it was served in a wheat basket.
Mushroom Tikka was well marinated, very juicy from inside and delicious(Recommended)
But the spotlight was on Paneer Koliwada, everyone loved it that we asked for one more serving.(Recommended)

For the main course we ordered for Veg Maratha, Paneer Khurchan, Dal Makhani and Dal Tadka.
Dal Makhani was amazing. Paneer Khurchan was fine but Veg Maratha is a definite show stopper, perfectly spiced, flavourful and aromatic, loved it.

For the desserts we ordered for Rabdi with Gulab Jamun and Chef Special Dessert of the day.
Chef special was really special. This dessert was served in a fruit salad bowl, it had yummy brownie crushed along with dry fruits and fruits.( Recommended).

Overall the experience at this place was good considering that I am a hardcore Non-veg lover.
The menu is set Moderately priced. Will visit again for sure!!!!!!!!!

Pathetic uncooked food. I ordered rotis, garlic Naan, paneer pulav and paneer handi from navratree Prasad through zomato and the quality of food was very pathetic that me & my relatives remained empty stomach even after paying so much for the food. I would not recommend this restaurant to anyone. They provide the food which is totally uncooked and quality is very low. I wish they had a negative rating system then I would have opted for the same. Worst experience till date.

It's a very good place to hangout...The Ghansoli one which I visited is great...service is good...but takes time to deliver food.. otherwise, it's a very good place for family and friends..they have two portion in restaurant..one Bar and another family.
We were sitting in the A/C hall and there were so many flies around us while we were having our meal. That was looking untidy. And to be very honest, I don't feel like having meal after that.

Good ambience good service food quality was decent good amount of varieties price is little too high for the kind of restaurant it is.
Overall good experience but not the best I have seen.

restaurants.address: C-WING, RB Mehta Marg, Sindhu Wadi, Ghatkopar East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400077, India

reviews.text: It's just hyped, if you are someone who loves a delicacy for its taste avoid the place

First of all the interior design, decoration and presentation is very cool. If i talk about the taste then i have never tasted such great South Indian dishes. They have maintained the best quality along with quality. Great deserts and best snakes corner i have ever visited. They are having lots of choices to have and we need to visit here many times to cover them all. At the last the service that they provided was so humble and nice. Highly appreciating and thankful for it. Will always recommend this place if you visit Ghatkopar. Never miss the chance to go and eat here.

Great place to visit if you love dosa. Their specialty lies in serving varieties of cheese dosas. They prefer serving it on the banana leaf which makes it even more attractive. Most of the dosas over here are served with coconut chutney and a bowl of sambhar. Staff is friendly and polite. They do have an outdoor seating. College students are the ones who visit this outlet quiet frequently due to which it’s horribly crowded. Average waiting time over here is somewhat around 30-40 minutes. 

Recommend dishes : 

1. Cheese-burst dosa
2. Cheese-burst masala maggi dosa
3. Chocolate sandwich
Compact dining area. Tried cheesy pasta it was good. Misal Pav was not at all worth trying. Staff was friendly and location is also good.

One of the best place . If you love cheese this is the place for you. Their cheese burst food is really famous. Their service is good. Food quality and quantity is really Best. The amazing Ambience and premium quality of food. Prices are bit high but quality of food balances it.

reviews.text: This place is located on the Main Street and one can find it easily. Scrumptious Foods. Really good place to hangout there. We were not satisfied with the service provided but food was tasty enough. Enjoy the food with some chit chat 🤤

Quirky superb place to visit specially for the food. They have amazing quality, quantity and taste of food. Their Signature dish of Spinach rice with Basilica sauce is a must must try. I am sure no one can be disappointed with that. The ambience is good and nice seating arrangement. There are tables with swinging chairs as well. The menu is quite interesting and so is its taste. Cheese Pav bhaji fondue, hummus with pita bread are another level dishes with make one crave for it.

This is the most memorable place. We somehow landed up to this place and woahh.
Its a bit small but the food is quite good and even the ambience. A small and cute place. I love it!

A good small cafe.
Outdoor seating needs improvement and maintenance.
Food is decent. Nothing extravagant.
Worth trying once.

reviews.text:
First Impressions were pretty good like the ambience, the menu, dance floor, etc. But they were not up to the mark. I feel there is a lot of scope for improvement. 
Ambience is very good with retro theme but i gound that seat covers were not clean. There were many starters but no one to make and serve the starter and I didn't find many options in deserts. Puppet show was just for the name sake it was that good. Although, the staff was very nice and polite.

Village – the soul of India is amazing place to hang out with families & organizing birthday parties. People can eat variety of chat items, mains, drinks, desserts around more than 55 items.. nice place for foodies. Food quality is not so good like 4 star restaurants but spending 2-3 hours with families here it totally worth it!!

I really liked the concept of having an all veg Buffet which would include all cuisines from different parts of India. Plus the ambience and overall vibe over here is desi and small things such as katputli dance, small one minute flok dance, chai over cycle, etc makes the dining experience even better. I even loved the service here as the waiter was friendly and very courteous.

If You Wanna Enjoy Those Relaxing Village Vibes In This Hectic City Life, Then "Village" Is The Must Visit Place For You!❤
It Is Located On Second Floor Of Growel's 101 Mall, Kandivali.
The Ambience Here Is Elegant And Beautiful With Specious Seating Areas.
It's A Perfect Place For Birthday Parties And Events.💞
They Have Too Many Entertaining Activities Over Their Like Puppet Shows, Jyotish Stall, Mehandi & Tattoo Stalls, Old Style Photo Studio With Funny Props Etc.
They Serve Tremendous Varieties Of North Indian, Rajasthani & Chinese Cuisine.💕
The Staff Here Is Welcoming And Friendly.😊
Nice theame restaurant with lavish buffet spreads across cuisines... Good ambience to spend few hours with family... Food quality is average but wide range of multi cuisine varieties to chose from.

reviews.text:

Guys!!

Pani puri shots 👉 Pani puri was tasty. And served in shots glasses.

Open pizza sandwich 👉 This was the most tasty dish drizzled with lots of cheese.

Mocktail 👉 Cranberry Surprise was prepared nicely.

Rabdi Jalebi👉 jalebi was crispy served with chilled rabdi and it was amazing.

All the food was presented nicely. Hygiene is maintained. Staff was friendly and service was prompt.

We would like to visit again.

Visited VEGGIES recently with mine friend and we had great time. It's heaven for veg lovers . Ambiance is awesome also management is very nice.
Service was quick , staff responded fast and was friendly . 
Fab place to visit with friends and family.

Coming to food we tried-
⏭️ MOCKTAIL
•PINK PANTHER -

Veggies Annex located in Kasarvadvli, Thane is very much known for their food quality, quantity and taste. The place serves a very wide variety of vegetarian food with best quality and taste. They have around 500+ dishes in their menu.

Food: 5/5
They have a great quality of food and they serve a very nice cheesy food.
Mocktail:
We tried Shagun and Fruit Punch from their Mocktail option. In milkshakes we tried butter scotch and dry fruit shakes. Fruits used are very fresh and it was very tasty. Consistency of shakes and Mocktail was perfect.
Starter:
In starter we ordered Alone Veg Allony, Cheesy Cigar, Paneer Burnt Chilly, Aflatoon Mushroom and Cheese Pav Bhaji. All of the starter are just mind-blowing it was very good in taste and it was looking very good in presentation.
Main course:
In main course we tried Veg Afgani with butter roti and cheese naan, it was really going very well with each other. Also we tried their thali which was very good in taste and it included two sabji with dal and rice and roti and one papad, in dessert they serve gulabjamun. Thali is very worth to try at low price, considering it's quality and quantity. The sabji is very good in taste.
Dessert:
They have a lot of options in dessert, we tried gadbad and kulfi falooda. It was very good in taste, it was full with nice cream, fruit, jelly and tutti fruti.

Ambience:5/5
Ambience very nice is very nice and calm with peaceful surrounding.

Service:
Their staff is very nice and courteous. Service is perfect and on time. Restaurant is very hygienic and table's are clean.

Recommendation:
Thali is best from their menu and in starters cheesy cigar is must try.

It was mind blowing place with decent ambience...

Starters and other foods are also yummy.

restaurants.address: Seth House,Ground floor Opera House, Charni Road East, Opera House, Girgaon, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400004, India

reviews.text: Decent vegetarian food right at the Opera House junction. The Velvet Zucchini with Basil soup was excellent, the crispy Lotus Stems was also fairly good. The Green Thai curry lacked the genuine Thai flavour and was so-so. Prices are reasonable considering the quantity. Service was a bit slow

I had been passing by this place for a while now and it was after a long time that I finally made it to this one. When looking at it from the outside, it looks like the perfect fine dining place with just the right amount of elegance. However, once you step inside, it is more casual and less business like. I was here with a group of friends and we had quite a few things here.

We started off with the Avocado Toastie which was crispy and delicious. A base of toast with guacamole is essentially what it was. It was bite sized and tasted pretty good but it wasn't extraordinary. It was not something that you would get a craving for, in the middle of the night.

The Botanical Bloom Bread was a delight. A huge loaf of bread was buttered up and stuffed with molten cheese and a flavor of garlic. It was crispy and the cheese sauce was just amazing. Bread and cheese is something that one can't really go wrong with and it was perfect here.

We even tried the Crispy Lotus Stem. It was slightly sweet and sticky. However, it tasted okay. The stem became chewy very quickly and it wasn't at par with the ones that I have had but it was a good effort.

We went for the Veg Exotica Pizza. It was loaded with veggies as the description stated and it was crispy, spicy and delicious. The toppings were good and it was well balanced with the amount of cheese. When it comes to pizza, the proportion matters and the proportion for this one was completely right.

Lastly, we tried the Avocado, Asparagus and Cream Cheese sushi. It was put together well and rolled up in white sticky rice with a slightly crisp centre of the avocado and asparagus. It was served with soya sauce and wasabi. The taste was almost perfect but it needed a bit more binding when it comes to flavor.

The place is decent and worth a shot if you like the way it looks. They have some unique dishes on their menu which are really good. They could work a bit more on enhancing their flavors and it could surely be on my list of the places to visit!

Ambience: 4/5
Food: 4/5
Service: 4/5

Sometimes its so easy to move away from the norm. I visited botanica with a group of girl friends and suffice to say that we couldn't be happier. 
Brand new, Botanica is so ideally located near Girgaum Chowpatty. It offers no booze and no meat. That is where the beauty starts.
They have an extensive menu. Indian, asian, continental and even fusion.
All mocktails and drinks are made with natural ingredients. Blue Pea, rosemary,thyme ,jalapenos, black tea, mint, chopped fruits ,you name it and they have a great drink.
served in pretty glasses, the drinks all taste good. Since we were so many, we could order different drinks and taste almost everything on the menu.
We tried Mexican Tomato soup, Miso and Green Latte. My miso soup had shitake . Well made and light.
The Asian delight was glass noodles in a mason jar. The wow factor was the smoke. And the smoke was in the cold salad. Each element....even the sesame seeds was so well flavoured. try the Mushrooms and mango or watermelon and feta salad if youre not keen on keeping it fresh and simple.
Zucchini cheese rolls were nice.
The assorted savoury cakes were a take on the kothambir wadi...with broccoli, yam etc. SO well made and the fried garlic crumbs made it even better.
The icing on the cake was the Rajma Galouti. So well smoked and so well smoked. For a second, I almost thought it was keema.
So worth the calories. you Must try this.
We had a dumpling platter. The drama and the plating....full marks to the chef. I liked the mushroom dumpling the best.
The greek pizza was super. Thin, crisp semolina base, cheese and arugula. Adult taste and awesome.
The chilli bbq jack fruit and asian spiced paneer baos were nice. Im not too fond of baos, so I didnt have more than a bite.
The sushi burger was super jazzy to look at. And on point for the sushi rice. But the paneer could be substituted with a crunch factor. That paneer made it mushy for me.
The jack fruit biryani was fragrant and nice.
As was the makhani ravioli. Pretty ,pretty and super yum, and bang on sauce.
The pumpkin tortellini with foam was  nice.
Dessert... theer was a chocolate with lemon grass pudding. I didnt get any lemon grass taste , but because I was full already, I didnt really miss the dessert. The basundi with rose balls...basundi with rooh afza caviar was nice.

A lot of chatting, good food and good times. And we took loads of pictures that I had to share. Go here and try all the chefs and servers recommend. They know their food

Go to botanica for a good time with family and friends.

The most amazing and perfect place for all vegetarian. The Botanica!!!
Nice and cosy place to have a perfect meal. The Botanica is located in cherni road, and its 10 minutes walking from the cherni road railway station. The place can be easily located on Google map as well.

The has really nice and cosy Ambiance with really cute sitting arrangement. The round tables, sofas and amazing dining experience. They also have different country clock displayed just to have a feel of international cuisines. The ambiance is really calm. The best part about the Botanica is their hospitality and lip smacking food. They have sitting capacity of around 80-100 people. The food can be at your table within 5 to 6 minutes after ordering.

The classy Ambiance and delicious food with super friendly and humble staff makes this place perfect for a meal with a family and friends. In the menu, around 90% of the dishes can be made jain.

We tried,
Mocktails: their range of Mocktails are really refreshing and amazing. As per their recommendation we tried Botanical martini, Miss mary. And bang on both were really amazing. The taste of jalapeño in martini was coming out well, the smoky flavor was good in miss mary. Overall both were really refreshing. 

Mexican tomato soup: A perfect start of a meal was a soup. All the flavors were coming out really nicely. The spicy, the tangy, little sweet. A perfect which can increase your craving. The soup had nachos and beans. A must try soup. 

Corn cottage cheese seekh: the kabab was perfectly cooked. The smokey flavors along with the flavor of corn and lots of cheese. The kabab was served along with cabbage and bell pepper salad and mint chutney. This was not that spicy. But was really soft. 

Asian spiced cottage cheese: again a perfect apittizer.. The rich red gravy of cashew and tomatoes along with small dices of cottage cheese and bell pepper. The perfect in taste and texture. The cheese was marinated properly and the balance flavors along with the drink was pure heaven. 

Arancini cheese poppers: this was something new in arancini. The cheesy poppers along with the salsa sauce and cheese cream. The best presented dish. The perfectly cheesy balls going well with the tomato salsa. 

In main course we wanted to try their kofta, as it was suggested by the staff. The kofta had a rich red thick gravy along with the Indian spices. The kofta was made-up from paneer and herbs. The quantity was sufficient. And can be eaten with Roti or biryani. We had missi roti, tandoori roti and Nawabi biryani.

The biryani was really rich and royal. The flavors were really amazing. Little more spicy then expected, but tasted really well. The rice was cooked properly and was not dry. The veg biryani lovers must try this here. the Indian herbs has enhanced the taste of the biryani. 

The last segment was THE DESSERTS 
Tiramisu: the mascarpone cheese along with vanilla cake and a strong flavor of coffee. This was mesmerizing and amazing. The taste was good. Coffee had a strong flavor in this dessert. Also, 

Melting chocolate cake: a melting lava cake was served along with the butterscotch ice-cream. The preparation was really like a melting chocolate. A dark flavored chocolate was just perfect and mouthwatering. 

Gold dust Cappuccino: Heard of this, but never tasted before. The Golden sprinkle on Cappuccino. This has made our meal. The edible sprinkle was garnished on the Cappuccino. The strong Cappuccino had a great taste along with the creamy milk. A must must try drink.

Overall had a great time with family. The staff has made our meal a great meal. Special thanks to @live_life_royal for amazing meal experience.

Botanica cafe and dinner is in girgaum opposite opera house near Chowpatty. Ambience was quite good and awesome. 

We ordered

1. Fruity flavoured beer. 
2. Watermelon and basil spritzer. 
3. Greek pizza. 
4. Stuffed mushrooms. 
5. Asian spiced cottage cheese. 
6. Crispy lotus stem. 
7. Chilli cottage cheese baos. 
8. Tiramisu. 
9. Melting chocolate cake. 

Ambience service food 5 on 5

reviews.text: Laughter is brightest where food is best." "Life is a combination of magic and pasta." "It's difficult to think anything but pleasant thoughts while eating a homegrown tomato." "One cannot think well, love well, sleep well, if not has not dined well

The ambience is decorated beautifully. The place is cool. Location is great too. It is located opposite central mall. Everything we had was delicious. Dishes were unique and tasty with good quantity. Hygiene was well maintained. Nyc staff and service.

KASBAH GRAND 

SEATING ARRANGEMENT & SERVICE ( 4/ 5 )
Located at top floor or I would say the rooftop area of chandiwala arcade, Goregaon west;  grand kasbah serves some authentic  dishes which includes the asian varieties, arabic, mughlai, indian. In Mansoon, its covered but on other days you can enjoy the lively atmosphere of rooftop. Has great decor and comfortable seating arrangement. This place don’t serves alcohol so you have to go with mocktails only. Staff were quite helpful and would help you on selecting your orders. Vallet parking is available but its at owners risk. 

We started with, 
Mocktails 
BLUE ALASKA:  ( 4 /5 )
It's a blue coloured drink. with a lot of crushed Ice.

GUAVA MARRY: ( 4 /5 )
guava juice with a twist of chat masala.

SUMMER DELIGHT:  ( 4 /5 )
a mix of orange juice along with cranberry juice

STRAWBERRY PUNCH: ( 4 /5 )
its was a milk-based drink with a flavour of strawberry.

QUEENS PUNCH: ( 4.5 /5 )
mild sweet orange juice with cranberry at the bottom.

BROWNIE OVERLOADED MILKSHAKE: ( 4.5 /5 )
It's a thick shake with milk and crushed brownie

We ordered some appetizers 
 
KOWLOON SPINACH WRAPPED CHICKEN : ( 4.5 /5 )
Chicken pieces wrapped with Spinach leaves and prepared with inhouse spices. Its tossed with chopped ginger and garlic. You get 7-8 pieces and tastes great.

LUCKNOWI SEEKH KEBAB: ( 5 /5 )
Our all time favourite, lukhnowi mutton seekh kebab. This would just melt in mouth. Served oved the sizzler plate.
 
MURGH TANDOORI KASHBAH: ( 4 /5 )
Unlike the traditional tandoori, here this is first tandoored to perfection and then is tossed in schezwan gravy. Chicken pieces were tender and its a spicy dish. 

SMOKED MACHLI: ( 4 /5 )
The dish is presented on Sizzler plate with silver foil covering with charcoal placed at middle & is surrounded with the Basa pieces . 6 pieces of Basa is marinate with turmeric based spice and is smoked to perfection. Few might not prefer the taste but as it has the hint of charcoal. 
  
CHICKEN WITH CASHEW NUT AND CORRIANDER : ( 4.5 /5 )
Boneless chicken pieces tossed along with Cashew nuts, Yellow - red Bell Peppers , Onions , Chopped ginger and garlic along with celery leaves. Its just amazing and something new. 

MURG DAHI LASOONI: ( 4.5 /5 )
Chicken Pieces marrinated with Curd, along with mixture of spices and Ginger garlic. Its then tandoored to perfection. Garnished with Lasooni dahi. Served over the sizzler plate. Superb taste.

PRAWNS KING TEMPURA: ( 3 /5 )
Deep Fried Prawns with a coating of Flour. The prawns tasted good but the coating was not cooked properly. Served with 7 pieces along with Mango chilly mayonise dip. A bit disappointment. 

THAI FLAVOURED GRILLED FISH: ( 4 /5 )
A Thai based preparation of Basa fish. The fish is marinated with spices and grilled. Garnished with Tangy Thai sauce. 6 pieces are served.

BALINESE BARBEQUE CHICKEN: ( 4.5 /5 )
Boneless chicken pieces without any coating is shallow fried and is tossed in balinese sauce. Placed over banana leaves and is served along with grated cabbage salad.  

In mains,
We tried the mains with Steam rice and Naan.
GOSHT PATIYALA: ( 5 /5 )
Absolutely wonderfull. Presented over miniature Flat tawa ; this dish is prepared with tenderised lamb pieces along with inhouse spices. This is a dry masala type dish. The prepared dish is Placed over a omelet & is served. A little disappointment in terms of portion size.
 
KORIYA PRAWNS:  ( 5 /5 )
The best prawns gravy one can ever try . A medium spicy Gravy which goes best with plain rice of Steam rice. With hint of coconut & spices, the dish just makes you more hungry. Portion size is good for 2 person.

SHREADED CHICKEN WITH GINGER ONION SAUCE :  ( 4.5 /5 )
Long slices of shreaded chicken prepared in ginger onion sauce along with yellow, red and green bell peppers. Garnished with spring onion leaves. Portion size can be shared among 2.

Finally,

In desert we had

KESAR FIRNI: ( 5 /5 )

GUL BAHAR SHAHI TUKDA: ( 5 /5 )

Visited Yeda Republic with a couple of friends lately. And I must say, the place is worth the hype. The ambiance is lit and has good music playing in the background. We had a couple of Lipstick and fruit shoot mocktail. 
Coming to the appetizers, we had tandoori chicken lollipop, veg corn nuggets which were scrumptious. Decided to have barbeque chicken pizza, spaghetti for main course. Looking forward to visit again and try the rest of the menu.

We tried-
Adraki
Sangria
Fruit Shoot
Chicken Seekh Kebab
Jalapeno Cheese Bites
Spaghetti
Chocolate Hazelnut Fondant

Yeda Republic in Juhu is undoubtedly one the quirkiest clubs in town. I've been a frequent visitor here and I've had one hell of a night every single time I've visited this place. They've come up with this new beautiful entrance which is decorated with golden fairy lights. They have a huge green wall opposite the entrance as its selfie point. Yeda Republic is an evil styled lounge bar with space suits and dark alleys. The lounge bar is located underground in the basement with Carribean flags with life like props wearing space suits, gas masks and respiratory pipes while you walk your way down. They have huge a jeep like structure located right in the centre where cute little staff members dressed up in spacesuits dance during weekends. Dark zones, Gas chambers, Ceiling with human bodies strapped with masks, ropes, jute bags, tunnel-like entry to the restrooms, waiters dressed like prisoners in orange one-piece suits are some of the traits of this lounge. The bar counter is clearly the highlight of this place with large cylindrical pipes which drop down from the ceiling and houses the Bar Bottles, for the rest of the display. They also have a fancy telephone booth with 5 ancient telephones. Talking about the food, the menu is a little compact when it comes to food. One thing they could work on is their menu. They have a wide bar menu but only 4 mocktails and 3 desserts in all. Also, I'd recommend y'all to place your order for maincourse and desserts along with the appetizers itself as they take a while to prepare the food.

We'd ordered :
In Mocktails :
1. Fruitshoot - Mixed fruits blended with sugar and vanilla ice-cream. The taste was good. If you like your drink sweet, you can opt for this one.

2. Lipstick - This is a tiny glass of mocktail having a very attractive red colour consisting of orange, mint, cranberry juice and peach crush.

In Cocktails :
1. Bloody Mary - This is our all time favorite, red colored spicy cocktail which will surely get you in the mood.

In Appetizers :
1. Cheese Corn Nuggets - Seven pieces of nuggets having melted cheese, corn and capsicum in its filling served with a dip. They are medium spicy in taste. 

2. Chicken Lollipop - Six pieces of chicken legs served with green chutney. They have a tangy taste. 

In Mains :
1. Chicken Sphaghetti Pasta with Pesto Sauce - They have three options in pasta base, ie. Sphaghetti, Macaroni and Penne Pasta. We'd opted for Sphaghetti Pasta in Pesto Sauce with chicken as its add on. It's served with two long garlic breads, garnished with cheese and black olives.

2. Chicken Makhani Pizza - This is a thin crust pizza which has Makhani sauce in its base topped with chicken pieces and cheese.

In Dessert :
1. Paan Falooda - I'm a huge paan lover so went for this one. This a satiating glass of falooda with paan syrup, jelly, almonds, cashews and french vanilla ice-cream.

It was a great excitement to visit here. 
We reached there by around 8:30pm.
The place is cool. Loved the ambience. 
Food was also amazing. 
We started with, 
*Lipstick Mocktail. 
** Fruit shooter. 
** Masala Fries. 
* Chicken Popcorn. 
* Hara Dhaniya Pizza. 
***  Chocolate Hazelnut Fondant. 
Masala fries was super tasty and fruit shooter was also great. Hara Dhaniya Pizza was good. And loved their chocolate hazelnut fondant. It was very amazing. Highly recommend.

reviews.text: A restaurant and bar situated in palm water club, kalyan, with great ambience and food. I went here with my family we were around 13 people. The food is good.. But service is bit on slower side..we went here for dinner. Price is on higher side.. Its better if you call them and reserve the table, especially on weekends.

Well, it was a favorite for our family until recently. The food quality had been going downwards but our last visit on Sunday, Jan 26 was an ultimate low. The restaurant is under renovation so we were asked to sit out in the garden accompanied by stray cats, hoards of mosquitoes and flies. I don't know what was worse, the sound and smell of flies and mosquitoes being electrocuted right at our table or smell of mosquito repellent or the pieces of coal in our nan or the stale paneer or the cold chicken soup. Eventually, I suffered from food poisoning, my brother had severe acidity. So yeah, it was an ultimate letdown. Just stay clear out of this one. There are better places available If you wanna spend a premium price for a dinner with fowl and flies around you. 2 stars just because it used to be nice in the past.

It's crowded on weekends

Biryani was ok ok type.. they take 20 minutes for serving the order wo keep dat in mind and order accordingly.. the waiters over here are not so responsive.. we paid the bill and was waiting for finger bowl but they was waiting for us to call them n ask for it.. so there is a room for improvement in service..

In short ambience is great with good quality food with the expensive rates..
All the best.. good day..

reviews.text:
Tea Villa Cafe in Kandivali has a far more vibrant setup as against the more traditional one.
F&B perspective, stays true to it's standards & delivers quality!
One of the very few places open late night, this outlet turned out to be out late night grub spot.
Our Order: Peri Peri Fries & Kit Kat Waffles

The new menu and new dishes added to the tea villa menu are really good. Not just that but the summer menu is good too. They come up with these seasonal menus which is excellent.

Tried a couple of dishes here from the summer and the new menu. Loved a few.

Do try the Sichuan Sliders. They were delicious. Crisp patty, spicy sauce.. one lipsmacking slider. The noodle bhel salad accompanied was to die for.

The potato wedges were crisp and delicious. Loved the seasoning.

Crispy cracker mousse from the summer menu.. creamy smooth Mushroom mousse and spicy guacamole topped over a crisp cracker. It was quite good. A balance of textures..  creamy, spicy, crispy and smooth.

Power protein salad from the summer menu.. this salad was delicious. Loved it. Chickpeas, Arugula, almonds, edamame and quinoa with a super delicious dressing.

Red and black combo from summer menu.. Manipur edamame black rice served with a coconut based chickpeas and Vegetable curry. This dish was delicious and healthy.

Sweet curd with mango .. from the summer menu.. a delicious yougurt with mango sorbet..I quite liked this one.

Chocolate Churros... Oh so good. Loved them. Do try!
Big fat churros drizzled with dark, milk and white chocolate and served with more Chocolate sauce.

Paneer Makhani sizzler... This one was decent..but my least favourite since I'm not a Makhani fan. The pulav was delicious. The paneer was melt in the mouth soft.. the gravy was a little sweet for my liking.

Cottage cheese rolls with Crunchy oats... These could have been better. The cottage cheese and the sauce within was delicious but the outer skin can be worked on.

Kashmiri kawah/twings and berries.. both the teas were good.

Overall a good experience.

Good place to experience..... Fantastic service..... Food is good, but not the best..... But a place to remember, specially for children. 
God interiors, unbelievable tea options.

Tea Villa Cafe is a great outlet for the people who are driving out for tea. Almost all varieties of tea are being served here made out of perfection and nicely breewed. The Ambience is awesome. One can have a great interaction session with their lovable once and it is also Idol to sit alone and complete your work assignment. I will visit this place again very soon.

Muscat bun with garlic tint and cheese sounded really fancy and we ordered one but didn't taste that great.. staff is really good and polite.. there is no parking available..

If you are looking for a restaurant serving authentic, good Local Non Vegetarian and Vegetarian Delicacies from Andhra Pradesh then Aavaky is the Great Choice!
Great Hospitality, Comfortable Seating Arrangements, Decent Interiors, Cool and Clam Ambience, Very Neat and Clean Premises, Hygienic Cooking Practices and Truly Authentic Andhra Food are some of the major reasons for The Foodies to visit here time and again!
Do Try Their Legendary Miryali Rasam, Drumstick Sambar, Mouthwatering Aavaky Vegetarian Biryani, Delicious Chicken 65, Andhra Royyalu Prawns Pulao, Andhra Mamasam, Bhendkaky Peanut Vepudu, Andhra Parathas and Many More!
If time permits, don't forget to taste their Signature Authentic Andhra Thali Meals which is available only during Lunch Time in the afternoon!
Good place for Andhra Food in Kandivali. Good taste and some fine options in veg and non veg. Staff was very humble and polite. Overall a nice experience.

A fine dining resturant in Kandivali food hub-Thakur village. Aavakay-The Andhra Kitchen as the name implies specializes for authentic Andhra cuisine. It is one of its kind place for fine dining.

Location/Ambiance: It is conveniently located considering crowd from Inox multiplex and foodies of Thakur village. Ambience is classy with luxurious confortable sofas. It is divided into compartments separated by pillars. Soothing background music adds to the experience.

Menu: They provide 4 different spices and 2 pickles which enhances the dining experience. They also give complimentary fried kurkure. Really crispy and in good portion.

Analysis-
> Mirapakay baji -
Mirchi pakoda stuffed with onions, tomato and chilli powder. I sprinkled some of the add on masala served alongside. They really enhanced the taste and flavour.

> Lemon coriander soup-
Diced veges simmered in veg broth. Consistency was thick and tastewise really good.

> Masala wada:
Deep fried wada made of chana dal and mix of spices. Wadas were sumptuous, fluffy and crunchy on oustside. Aftertaste was spicy. Highly recommended!

> Drumstick sambar-
Popular South Indian dish- cooked with toor dal, chopped onion and tomatoes. Drumsticks were properly cooked. Really delicious, flavorful and healthy sambar.

> Tomato rice-
Masala rice made with tomato, onion, dal and spices. It was slightly spicy but taste extremely good. Comfort food.

Overall this place can be visited for quality family fine dine experience. Definitely vising in near future to try their non veg food and other dishes.

reviews.text:
Gustoso was recently renovated and hence we went to check it out. The ambience is beautiful like a bar in Italy. In some sections you can sit right next to their open kitchen. We ordered a Diavola pizza. The pizza was brilliant is every sense. Perfect bread, beautifully done tomato base and the meat was spectacular. The spaghetti carbonara was a downer. Have had much better. Lastly the Chocolate Gelato was smooth lingering on the palate. Loved it. 
Overall felt the prices have rocketed.

Gustoso is an amazing Italian restaurant located at Gowalia tank which serves authentic italian food. It's a beautiful cozy place with good music. Seating arrangement is really nice and service is amazing. Very friendly and Cooperative staff. Valet is available.

Food we ordered.

Minestrone soup (5/5)

Bruschetta (5/5)

Five cheese platter (5/5)

Indianapoli (we got some rocket leaves as add ons) (5/5)

Panna Cotta (5/5)

Espresso croquant (5/5)

Espresso (5/5)

Hot toddi (5/5)

We had wonderful experience here. I would highly recommend this place.

The fried king prawns and the kalamari was absolutely heavenly to the palate
The garlic bread with cheese finger licking
The pasta superb
The pizza never had anything like this 
Just too amazing 
Perfect blend of spices chicken and the crust too good
The salmon succulent and delicious

Dined last night at the newly renovated Gustoso, Kemps Corner. What’s changed- Prices have skyrocketed and portion sizes have become half. It’s one thing to raise prices, but to make portions so small that they don’t even satisfy one person is really ridiculous! The pizzas are the only saving grace. Alcohol prices are also absurdly high. One can’t even enjoy a decent glass wine below Rs.1000 per glass. The management seems to have the misconception that they are some Michelin star fine dine restaurant! They need to come back to earth or people will stop patronising soon. 
The earlier decor was bright and cheerful but now it’s become really dark and dingy, more like a lounge bar. Seriously wonder what the management is doing.
Service is too slow...they keep their costumer's waiting fo food for mor than hr wich is not acceptable...very much disappointed by the service 👎

reviews.text: Superb food . They'll severe according to your convenience. Must try!! Very tasty 😋

Amazing cafe with lots and lots of great menu options. I specially loved the smoked chicken and harissa chicken there. As well as the side of fries is just amazing. The place is very easy to find and the ambience is really rustic with an extremely cozy yet somehow an homely feel to it. First impression of the dessert options was just amazing. Moroccan Pulled Chicken Burger - This Burger had a tikki of shredded chicken added with fresh tomatoes & lettuce and served with french fries & mayo. Good Taste (4/5)

Golden Fried Prawns - These were very basic in taste & the taste can be improved. (3/5)

Hazelnut Affogato - This cold beverage is one of the best you can here. This was the espresso coffee topped with Vanilla Ice cream & Hazelnut Syrup. The mixture of this tasted perfect. (4/5)

A good place where you can go on dates as well as hangout with your buddies.

Garlic bread is worthless but both the pizzas were superb and it's too filling. Toppings are added graciously over here. The cheese burst add-on is definitely a must have. No complaints for pizzas, only cheese garlic breads needs to be improved. Packing is nice and proper. Time taken to prepare and deliver is proper.
We ordered pizza many times from this place. Spicy chicken tikka pizza is really very tasty but problem is with packaging only.

reviews.text: Most restaurants are nowadays not delivery the food cause of high number of COVID 19 but Box8 DM's are doing superb job in delivering the food During lockdown you will not found any Quality and Quantity issue
Great food for students and people who live away from home. Chicken biryani is good too.

If you are coming late from the office around 12:00 Am and your wife has not cooked anything or because of the uninvited guest, the food is over then you can order from the Box8 and you will get the Fresh and Real Desi food within 30 minutes
Which containers and Boxes they are using trust me its fully air tight container. Good packaging ever in food chain industry this restaurant use Biodegradable plastic which is good for environment

The place is located in the film city road. It is a delivery kitchen...
They have great and best options available here for vegetarians and non vegetarians...
It is well known for north indian food and Biryani. They also have sandwiches, paratha wraps, desserts available here...
I love their fusion box the most and i have mentioned 3 fusion box which i had...
I ordered my food from here and the food was prepared and delivered before time which is a good sign...

We had 3 curries..
Daal Makhani is the one you should definitely order from here. The amount of makhan in it was perfect, and the perfectly cooked and absolute amount Red Kidney Beans and Whole Black Lentils making the dal makhni astounding...
I also had "Amritsari Chole Curry" and "Kadhai Paneer Curry". Both were perfect to order and good in taste. The pieces of paneer in Kadhai Paneer Curry was perfect the only problem was the amount of spices in it was too much...
All the above curries were served with a green chutney and onion salad...

We had 3 fusion box....
They serve salad, curd, rice, green chutney and curry in it...
I had "Dal Makhni Rice", "Dilli Wale Rajma Chawal" and "Paneer Makhni". Dal makhani rice box and rajma chawal box are amazing.... Paneer Makhni box is also nice, but gravy in it is in less amount. Else the taste was perfect...

Dal makhni 5/5. (must order)
Amritsari chole curry 4/5.
Kadhai paneer curry 4/5.
Dal makhni box 5/5. (must order)
Dilli wale rajma chawal box 5/5.
Paneer makhni box 4/5.

reviews.text: Classy and calm place. Amazing way to spend the afternoon, by the race course. Food is equally awesome here. The taste is quite authentic and sumptuous. Quantity is decent enough too, for the price and the view. Only the service can be more prompt, especially the senior staff. Else, a great place to spend time

The restaurant, located inside the Mahalaxmi race course, gives an amazing view of the entire place. While you can enjoy the mouth watering food inside, you can enjoy the lush green view of the race course. I would recommend it for a lunch outing, rather than dinner, since the view is breathtaking in the day. Gorge on their kebabs or continental surprises, as all come as perfect for the taste buds. It's ideal for a romantic date in the heart of the city.

Ambiance is perfect, with the old structure and long hanging chandeliers.
It definitely has the old world charm and it surely is one of the best located places that we have in mumbai, with overlooking the race course.
Coming to food - well, it was good food, nothing to complain about. However the service was terrible and sloppy as the servers at our table were having an argument about something and was not something with listening to.

Fantastic location and well maintained place . I dint feel like i was in Mumbai . Amazing food. The place was all greenish . Indian food was yummy. Just for the beautiful cozy atmosphere and food , I recommend you to visit this place .  How ever staff deserve 1/10 rating. I was trying to make an order and staff dint even bother to come and was postponing my order asking me to wait more etc . It took 45 mins for them to come to my table and take order !!!! Such a rude behaviour. Recommend you to take appointments early as place can be crowded on weekends .

The restaurant is situated in mahalaxmi race course so this place is green and has a great and chilled climate because of the trees the ambience near the restaurant is amazing the ambience of the restaurant is very much classy the bar table looks very awesome and the food we had was panner shashlik which was amazing the price is overpriced but it's worth it and visit this place during evening time

reviews.text: Nice place to visit and to have a good time spend. With family and friends. Mostly events are managed over here and they have special lounge for parties. The place is very friendly and even staff is curtious. Nice place to go for a date. Nice place do visit once

'Keiba' the Jap name points to horse race, as located at Mahalaxmi, and highlighting the horse stable in the outlet.

Cuisine- Pan Asian
Service/Category/Style- Family-friendly/Bar/Casual Dining
Ambience- Lively, Ambient Lights, Live counters
Staff- Courteous but inarticulate and not well-trained
Well Known for- Sushis, Live prep

The spacious outdoor and indoor seating areas, high-octane bar and chic décor are eye-catching and exude a warm vibe. The hard rock music suits well with the decor of the outlet. The menus are exhaustive and there is a separate one for vegetarians and non-vegetarians. Apparently in the kitchen too, the sections are strictly divided. The bar menu is equally an exercise in choices. The food here is replete with fresh, high-quality ingredients, yet all dishes do not hit the right spot. It is the service here which mars the dining experience as the staff is inarticulate and not well-trained.

Our orders:
- Chilli Chicken (balanced spice)
- Chicken Dimsum
- Prawn Dimsum
- Crab stick Sushi (winner, with the juicy fresh crabs)
- Stir fried Noodles with Chicken
- Pineapple Piscour (best cocktail of the day)
- Red Wine Sangria
- White Wine Sangria

• Overall - 4
• Food - 4.7

Regular water is special as it comes in copper utensils, comes with a tag of advantages about the utility of it. The hotel staff is very warm and courteous.

A restaurant which gives you the good South Indian vibe, with the Ambience and theme with the people working around with the lungis, and  water served in copper vessel and the good food after all .. I had the gunpowder squid fry , Sri Lakhan lollipop , and kori Ghassi , steam rice in main course.. Must visit you want to have a south Indian vibe with good south Indian food

Pricing is too high.....for example biryani was about Rs 475 for two person....and other dishes I order was above Rs 400/-

Chicken tikka was awesome.

Try Basa Tava fry... This is one of my favorite.

But chicken curry was not up-to the mark. Chicken was half cooked and curry was also tasteless....we raise the complaint then they provided other one.

And finally we order chicken dum biryani... Which was total disappointment....no taste again chicken half cook..... 

I suggest if you are planning to visit try the starters or dessert.

Or  provide instructions to the cook or manager before ordering.....

Also the standards of cutlery cleanliness is not upto the mark as we had to replace the 2 glasses and 3 plates as they had some stains / specks on them. After a tiring weekday routine, we were looking for a place to relax. Stumbled upon The Lab, Malabar Hills with a chill vibe and good food. 
Starting off with Cheese Corn Balls, crispy and well coated with creamy mixture. An all vegetarian outlet definitely calls for these!
Moving onto the Pink Sauce Pasta, we felt the taste was super homely and comforting. Every bite was a delight.
The Pizza Margherita was average but overall the food was extremely reasonable for the price. 
PS. They have games and comfy mattresses to help you destress!
Lovely place to chill with friends. The staff is friendly offering quick service. They have board games. The food is damn delicious. A must visit place.

reviews.text:
Considering the lockdown and takeaway situation, I wasn't expecting too much from Joey's this time round. But I am so glad that I had a surprisingly amazing experience with the takeaway! We had ordered beforehand and reached there post half an hour to collect our order, I think it was a wise choice to do so because the place was crowded. Luckily for us, our order was ready when we reached and it made a lot of difference since we didn't have to stand amongst the crowd and could stay socially distant too! 
We ordered cheese garlic bread, plain cheese pizza, garden fresh pizza and veg supreme pizza. All were hot and fresh and absolutely yummy! Would recommend you to pre-order in case you're doing a takeaway.

This place has some of the best pizza in town. They have a vast variety in both veg and non veg pizza. The staff is also polite an help us is choosing the perfect pizza. The price is reasonable and the quantity is also enough. Also, it has another outlet in Andheri. My all time favourite place. Surely a must visit place for all pizza lovers😍

Very famous for pizzas in the suburbs.
Currently serving only takeaways due to lockdown guidelines.

Average delivery time on weekdays is 30-45 minutes, weekends 45 minutes to an hour.

China gate and chicken tikka pizza in cheese burst are must haves.

Chicken garlic bread is also awesome.

Slightly on the pricier side but bang for buck!
Mouth watering varieties, doesn’t cheap out on toppings, fresh veggies, very hygienic and polite staff.
They cheese bust pizza and you feel you are drinking cheese. And taste is too good. New bees should try. Long way to go. But too crowded pre covid.

Food is not very great regular causal dinning dished but the quantity is pretty good. Music is also good. Not too loud not too low. So all n all a thumbs up 👍

reviews.text: Kyani & Co. Is the best breakfast place I have ever eaten at. Such simple food and such amazing taste were enough to satisfy my breakfast needs. The old structure of the place gives a very authentic look to this place. A must visit.

Kyani & Co. , the famous Irani cafe in the city, located at JSS road near Metro Cinema Junction. Kyani Bun Maska, Irani chai, keema pav are the BEST, and most importantly the restaurant is pocket friendly, always jam packed during all working hours.
It remains one of the few places in the city where you can grab a wholesome breakfast for less than Rs. 100, Irani Chai is so so so good. With the bun maska they just go so well together.
The best Irani Outlet that exists.If you are going do try out Chai and Bun Maska for sure.

Kyani & Co is quite famous Irani Cafe and bakery located in Fort, Mumbai Maharashtra India 
This place is very famous in locals and travelers. 
Kyani basically known for their low rates as compared to modern cafes. 
Kyani Bun Maska, Irani chai, keema pav is very famous, and they serves so many items in both Veg and Non-Veg at very low rates.
I visit this cafe to taste their food and I tried out Chicken Patties, Chicken Bhurjee, Chicken Cutlet, Bun Maska, Irani chai, and Pineapple cake.
All the items which I tired out it's too good in taste.
Whenever you visit this cafe you surely enjoy alot with their Vintage looks, Low rates, fast service, kyani too much focus on hygiene.
One of the oldest cafe in mumbai. Cost is affordable. Old architecture

Valet parking available for a fee.

Only the terrace area has smoking allowed.

B Bhagat Tarachand, Mulund.

Who hasn't heard bout B Bhagat Tarachand?!! You will hardly find anyone!. It's famous since generations & widely spread across Mumbai!. We had been here recently again, situated@N.S. road, near Panch Rasta, Mulund West!.

The surrounding ambience has pleasing vibes & aroma is soothing too!. The decors are well lit & gives the feel of its long lavish legacy of generations!.

The staff here is very friendly & prompt while placing several orders & suggestions & serving hot too!.
Dharmendra, incharge for our table was very attentive to recommend & serve with delight!.

Let's checkout the food we had ordered here, 

Papad Churi was totally crunchy & tossed up with onion & chaat!. You just can't stop after one bite!.. It's all time regular favourites for most of the tables!. Surely try this dish for starters!.

We next ordered Chinese Platter, it was finger licking & platter had sufficient quantity for sharing wise!. Several Chinese items include manchurian balls, Vej crispy, paneer chilli & spring rolls & salad in sidings!.

We also had Paneer Tikka Dry, it was mouthwatering to glance & craving for more!. The spices were nicely blend & paneer was coated crisply & lip smacking!.

Paneer Cheese Tikka, is a nice fusion of seasoned paneer & over loaded cheese!. If you love both, surely go for this tikka, it's finger licking awesome!.

Bhagat Tarachand Special Thali  gives a glimpse of its succesful tradition it carries!. Balanced so well with ghee chapatis, 2 sabji of own choice, papad, dal, raita etc!. It's wholesome & flavourful by all means!.

Gulab Jamun is tender soft & sweet to its core, lingering sweetness for a long time to cherish!. Surely good to try Gulab Jamuns for dessert!.

Icecream slice looked tempting & every slice of it was yummm!! After heavy dining, it's truly a bliss to pounce on desserts like this for sweet tooth lovers!.

B Bhagat Tarachand is a proven excellence & you surely visit this place quite often to experience it's awesome treat & hospitality!. Thankyou!. ❤

Not any more. The quality of food has gone from bad to worse. The service and customer interaction is pathetic. 
I ordered 4 garlic naans today and I got unpeeled full pieces of garlic on all my naans. Anyone from the restaurant business would never ever do this. I would cancel their license for such a shameful approach to managing orders.
When I called to complain, instead of saying sorry, he said you keep that naan and we will exchange a new one for you in return. I banged the phone... last time order from my side.
Delivery ordered through Zomato. Medu vada and masala dosa was good. Idli as seen in the photo was stuck and little hard.
Nice interior design of the restaurant. Good food, ordered a variety of starters. Think my favourite was the manchurian. Friendly staff too

reviews.text:
We ordered

1) For Starters - chicken tandoori
The pieces were extremely tasty and juicy served with green chutney and good portion of salad.

2) For Maincourse - Chicken Kolhapuri in gravy with Wade

The gravy was up to the mark and tasted really well when combined with bites of wade.
I came to know here that Wade in Maharashtran food are a bit similar to fried puris.

Quantity sizes are good. You will exit this place with your belly extremely full, feeling drowsy.

A great place to eat for college students and families as well.
The seafood is delicious, especially the prawns were the best I have had in Navi Mumbai.
The service was quick and the ambiance is excellent. 
Also, try Butter Chicken. The chicken was as soft as it can get.

I ordered pudina kebab and mutton masala fry from this restaurant. Food was quite impressive, fresh and flavourful. Kebab was very soft, spicy with some salad and pudina chutney. Mutton was breathtaking, mutton just melts into your mouth with hot gravy. It was a perfect dish for a non veg lover. Service was good. Delivery was prior its time. Good quality food is served here. I would suggest everyone to try mutton dishes from this restaurant.

Maharashtra Lunch Home is an amazing place in the suburb region of Nerul, navi Mumbai.
They serves delicious North indian, Chinese, Malwani and sea food cuisine.
They have speciality in amazing  malvani food and sea food.
We have ordered,

- Paneer Biryani 
  Have sufficient amount of marinated paneer cubes along with spices and it served with the onion-tomato raita. premium quality rice was used and the quantity was sufficient for two people.

- chicken Tikka Masala
   The chicken pieces are so juicy and it was nice with quantity as it sufficient for 2 to 3 people. The taste was really mouth watering.

- paneer Tikka Masala
  In this the paneer chunks are used along with the capsicum and tomato pieces having proper amount of masala with good quantity. It was so tempting.

Overall experience was really very awesome. They have both dine in facility and fastest delivery service.
I must recommend this amazing outlet for their variety of  delicious food items 😋.

This place is just amazing.!!!!
We had a Great time here.
Best place for all nonveg lovers, Especially for Seafood lovers.
This outlet is not too far from Nerul Station.
Ambience was quite good.
Service was fast and efficient.
Now talking about the food we had, firstly the starter we ordered was Bombil Rava Fry. The crunchy texture outside & soft bombil inside was just yum with Green Chutney.!!
Bombil is a must try.
Main cource was Surmai Thali & Prawns Masala Fry with Vade.
The thali was a perfect meal. One can have a wholesum food by having thali here with surmai fry, rassa, bhakari, rice, solkadi, sukat. 
The taste of surmai fry & rassa was typical konkani style. We loved it.!!
The refreshing Solkadi was Best.
Now About Prawns, it looked so tempting & mouth-watering. The taste was really amazing. The prawns were well cooked. 
They have a sufficient quantity of food according to the price. 
The place was crowded & people were standing outside in waiting. This says it all.!!
We had A Great Time. We enjoyed every bit of it.

reviews.text: The food here is very good and tasty. They maintaine cleanliness very strictly and the staff is very polite . Their hotels environment is so good that makes you feel like I should go again. The prices are reasonable according to the taste of the food and u will not regret going there

Neel Kamal was good previously and now too it makes its iconic dishes perfectly. The Murg Mussalam , butter chicken, noodles, fruit punch and other bunch of starters are perfect. But after the renovation I visited the place and I asked them what’s new food items. He said the same old dishes and when I asked what’s new other than tht, then he did not have any clue. I asked for a new kebab type starter for which he suggested chicken ghee roast. It was not good, there was no taste of ghee nor was it roasted, you can see in the picture that it wasn’t served like a kebab but like a main course side dish. Taste wasn’t upto the mark. I also ordered a fruit punch to set my mood, which was classic, tasty! But nothing new in the drink menu. For main course I ordered Chicken Patiyala, and I have to say that it was the most uninteresting looking dish I have had. Chicken patiyala consists of a base of chicken stuffed omelette which is topped with a great tasting gravy. But here at neel Kamal, it was just a plain chicken curry and they topped the whole subzi with a huge omelette. We literally found just omelette in the dish, there were like 4 small pieces of chicken in the dish. The quality of the restaurant got degraded. The ambience of restaurant has been pretty good. I wish they try to change their dishes and add new menu items with a well versed waiters.

reviews.text:
So I have been Here a Couple Of Times And For Many Such Amazing Ensemble of Weddings, Tried their various buffets but the best I found was this Indo-Continental Mix Cuisine they serve.

It included salads, Raitas, Biryanis, Etc . All of them were flatteringly amazing . The exquisite set of Desserts and Sweetdishes include stuffs as per your concern. From pan shots, Mastanis to what not . Every nook and corner of countryland cuisine is taken into consideration here.

Starting with food it is delicious and affordable with approx ₹450 per plate. The food is heaven for all the veg lovers with large variety topped with hot & fresh serving. The cleanliness is next to nothing at this budget and clesrly is s notch higher thsn other Indian restaurants and Hotel. 
Secondly the stay is a delight. You will not get a sigle chance to complain with a very polite staff!

Had been here for marriage in 1st floor ac hall. It can accommodate approximately 300-350 people at a time. Hall is spacious. The catering was decent not extra ordinary as such. The evening reception had one type of mushroom starter with kokam and one more welcome drink. Kokam hardly had the kokam flavor in it. Did not try the second drink. Mushroom cheese starter was ok ok types. The main course had panipuri at the start comprising of both cold water Pani Puri and hot ragda Pani Puri. The other items were phulka, naan, puri, mix veg bhaji, paneer masala, akrodh halwa(super heavy and delicious), malai cheni, veg biryani, raita, salad, papad, pickle, chana, tomato, cucumber, beet, etc. There was another sweet which looked like made from sewai. Lastly, the course summed up with roasted almond ice cream and butter milk. Overall ok and definitely could have been better.

reviews.text:
Overall service 5/5
Top notch place with a very reasonable rate and great dishes together which makes it a treat to the eye. Great eye catching food with good presentation. Tasty and thus hot and fresh served. Good choice of cold drinks available too. Small cozy and thus very comforting ambiance with soothing music and thus a view of the peddar road along the window. Best place to chill with friends. Awesome service. Thanks.

Indizza The Delivery Kitchen located on peddar road, next to vama road.
Serving best food in south mumbai to your door step.
Order your food now from zomato.
We had the following food items:

•Paneer Pahadi Tikka- 5/5
Tikka had an enticing flavour and the masala used ensured a well balanced taste.

•Pudina Nimbu Pani- 5/5
This drink is heaven. It was so refreshing and soothing.
This drink is basically a mixture of pudina, rocksalt, sugar and lemon.
A must try for all.

•Chicken Achari- 5/5
Chicken cooked with pickling spices to give a tangy flavour.

•Chicken Tikka Biryani- 4/5
Keep calm & enjoy the delicious chicken tikka biryani.
This biryani had loads of chicken tikka perfectly marinated, garnished spices for its flavoring in fragnant rice and topped with fried onions.

•Dal Makhani- 5/5
This is one of my favorite punjabi dish.
Dal topped with cream was so delicious and yummy.
I enjoyed this Dal with cheese chilli parotha.

•Murg Tikka Lahori- 5/5
Murg lahori chicken tasted so well. 
Finely chopped tomotoes and a perfect mix of spices.

•Junglee Naan- 5/5
This was something unique.
It had garnished garlic and mint leaves that will give you such a taste you won’t be able to resist.

•Laccha Paratha- 5/5
This paratha was a whole wheat paratha which tasted good with murg lahori tikka and dal makhani.

I’d recommend people visiting here to try their yummy starters, junglee naan, pudina nimbu pani, dal makhani and murg lahori tikka.

This place is located on the main road just opposite wood land apartment. It is easy to find this restaurant. We visited this place on Friday there are two restaurants at the same place one is Indizza and the other one is Pav-O-Licious both of these place have same kitchen same dining area The ambience is not so big but the interior issue just awesome there are creative things done on the walls there was one bicycle hung up on the wall and Food written on the wall with the help of that bicycle. Walls are painted with nice colours and ambience is too good they have the live kitchen which can be seen from dining area the only thing we dint like was the AC was too slow of this place. Coming to the food.
🔘WHAT WE HAD
1) Gooey Chocolate
2) Butter Laccha Paratha
3) Butter Junglee Naan
4) Chicken lababdar
5) Chicken Tikka Biryani
6) Chicken Achari Roll
7) Basil Chicken Tikka
8) Mali Chicken Tikka
9) Nimbu Pani
.
The food quality and quantity both was good taste was also good The paratha was soft and taste was good. I loved the junglee Naan. Chicken lababdar was just awesome with tha naan. Biryan was ok not so good. Achari roll was good. Basil chicken tikka was bit Spicy but Malai chicken tikka was the best.
⭕PRICE
1) Gooey Chocolate = Rs 125/-
2) Butter Laccha Paratha = Rs 65/-
3) Butter Junglee Naan = Rs 100/-
4) Chicken lababdar = Rs 320/-
5) Chicken Tikka Biryani = Rs 355/-
6) Chicken Achari Roll = Rs 245/-
7) Basil Chicken Tikka = Rs 205/-
8) Mali Chicken Tikka = Rs 205/-
9) Nimbu Pani = Rs 45/-
.
Price is not so high but quality food must visit.
.
Great place nice experience would love to visit again. ❤️

A delivery kitchen with a dine in option, we tried Indizza Delivery Kitchen, Peddar Road.
Quaint, little outlet with an open kitchen for the customers to get an insight into the cooking, it was a lovely experience. 
We chose to order the Basil Mushroom Spinach and Cheese starter along with Chicken Achari Tikka. The mushrooms were heavenly and left us salivating for more! The chicken was spicy and a little salty due to the flavour combination of acchar but definitely succulent. 
Jumping onto our absolute favourite Butter Chicken, we decided to pair it with Chilli Cheese Naan and Stuffed Chur Chur Kulcha. The gravy was creamy and sweet, great quantity with bite sized pieces of chicken which we loved! More so the naan with the perfect amount of cheese. The kulcha could be savoured all by itself with the masala stuffing. 
We would absolutely suggest this place for a wholesome and happy meal!

I have always been a big fan of Indizza - The Delivery Kitchen ever since it opened in Worli! Had ordered for food from there and was really impressed! Was excited to hear that they recently opened a delivery and takeaway outlet near Vama, Kemp's Corner Flyover, Pedder Road! And finally I decided to visit this new one.

First thought, I would do a takeaway, but there is space for about 6 to 8 people to sit and eat at the outlet. So thought might as well do that! This outlet delivers to places in the radius of 4 kms or so, which means pretty much entire of South Mumbai. Indizza serves North Indian food - Appetizers, Rolls, Curries, Dal, Rotis and Desserts! In short a wholesome meal. They have reasonable amount of Veg and Non Veg options which I believe would cater to all.

Talking about what all I tried at Indizza -

We started with few starters - Bharwaan Mushroom Tikka, Paneer Jeera Mirch Tikka and Aloo Achari Tikka. I would personally recommend these starters in the same order. Mushroom Tikka is too good, lipsmacking! In case one doesn't prefer mushroom, then one should go for Paneer Jeera Mirch Tikka, there are other options as well in Paneer Tikka. Paneer was soft and all appetizers came along with Pudina mint chutney and some onions. Aloo Achari lacked the taste though.

We ordered for some drinks. Besides the regular soft drinks they serve Nimbu Pani and Pudina Nimbu Pani! Nothing fancy about it and the drinks were also served in basic bottles, but effective and refreshing taste to go along with the food!

Next from the rolls section, we ordered the Paneer Makhani Roll, wrapped neatly in an aluminium silver foil. Rolls are served in tandoori or Roomali roti! We had this roll in Roomali Roti. Yummy, the filling was too good, roti cooked well. No complaints at all. Would recommend people trying rolls as per their likings and preferences.

Moving to the mains, we ordered for Dal Makhani, Paneer Tikka Masala. From the Rotis, I was really excited to try the Truffle Cheese Naan. Naan was cut in a way Pizza is cut. Stuffed with regular cheese flavoured with Truffle. Truffles have garlicky flavour and a peculiar aroma. I personally loved it, some may feel it to be pungent. So please use your discretion. For me Truffle Cheese Naan was the Highlight or Star of the evening! Dal Makhani creamy - rich - thick, perfect in taste. Paneer Tikka Masala adequately spiced and rich in flavour! What an awesome meal.

Finally turned to desserts, tried the Gooey Chocolate. Served in a basic container, but loved the chocolate crumbles and topping on fresh swedish chocolate cake! Divine and perfect way to end!

I am happy, that I decided to have my meal there rather than takeaway. Liked the overall experience, staff was courteous, Mr. Vijay was helpful! Would recommend all, do try Indizza, definitely worth every penny that you spend!

reviews.text: Ordered home from here yesterday and the pizza was delicious. They have interesting combinations of pizzas such as the Popeye pizza- which has spinach, onion and feta as toppings. This is a really unique combination but it works really well together. We also ordered the Bombay pizza which had onion and capsicum. We added truffle oil to this  which made it even better! They have many options to add on to the pizza as well. My favourite was the garlic oil which we added on almost all the pizzas and it was delicious. We also got the margarita pizza which is a classic but was still really good! All the ingredients they use are high quality which makes the experience even better. We also got the garlic cheese bomb which is super cheesy and unique. It comes with a spicy capsicum dip as well and is a definite must try if you go there! Although, the food was great I feel it had become very cold and rubbery by the time it came home and it would have been way better if we ate it there. Also, the food was delivered later than the time mentioned. But this place is definitely value for money and I will be ordering again.

Fantastic pizza and cookies. The salad and drinks are yummy too. I haven’t eaten a single thing here that I didn’t like. They deliver but I’d recommend that you go to the shop, meet the team and see how everything is prepared from scratch. Also their garlic bomb is the shizz. Go Viking!
Excellent Pizza 🍕 from base to all kinds of sauces are made there itself by GENIUS chef Simon Barton.
Awesome Pizzas!!! Simple menu with crazy style of Pizzas!! Lip smacking...wonder how they landed in Our tiny lane of Prabhadevi
Best pizza with the veg taste looks goods. Fresh bread dough which crisps.

reviews.text:
Good food & well spoken staff 👍
 Have visited many times...
Highly recommended place for a quick bite. Quick service with no compromise in the flavours. Staff is affectionate and welcoming. Do visit. Tandoori dishes are a must try.
Went to this joint after very long time chicken BBQ pizza I finger leaking good. Love to have pizza from so many years. Affordable restaurant. Best place. Have been here so many times.

Its a good joint for usual quick bites..  However as my experience the food could be called average..

In terms of the Ambience it was alright as the space is little small, although customers kept coming, the place was a little busy !

The cooking time was too much.. It almost took 20 mins for the starters to arrive.. 😌

We tried to be on a safer side and called for *Chilli Potatoes*. The dish was really good in terms of taste.. This is the dish which actually saved the night if you could say!

We also orderd Chilli Garlic Noodles, however the noodles seemed to be dry, and didn't bring out the Garlic taste much, however it was chilly as per the name !

Staff were really helpful though 🙂
So yummy best food👌

reviews.text: Good ambiance and quality of food is good. Good destination if you want to have veg food. Customer service is a bit slow and people don't respond to your concerns in time.

Well, this place will give you both an authentic indian food and a fascinating italian or mexican bowl. The owner, Shruti she's amazing and will take care of all your needs. A family place, this is perfect for group dining meals as well. I loved the Mojito, Teda Meda their famous drink, Pav bhaji fondue & the sizzler as well. Would love to be here again super soon. Plus, they have zomato gold 🤩

The decor is really fancy, and colourful. Music was outdated (or maybe cz we went on lunchtime... irrespective service should be same ) The pesto paneer was very bland like absolutely no flavour.  Open wada pav was okhay but it tasted more like a pizza than wadapav. I feel the place is a little bit too expensive for the food they provide. It's not bad. But it's not amazing either.
Great place, great food.. Amazing ambience and a worth place to.chill at!!

Good ambiance..PH se Food is a lively restaurant located in mulund on mulund goregaon link road in Runwal greens. Nice and lively location.. They serve in very unique style with unique dish name. Price is moderately kept. You can get Jain items there. They have interesting variety of salad n pav bhaji..we had 3 idiot combination of rolls with different stuffing and sauces, pavbhaji platter, zucchini role, jain vadapav and last but not the least sizzling brownie though I didn't like brownies.
