reviews.text: It's fresh...it's tasty and there's variety!! The Ambience is beautiful too!! I totally recommend this place for those people who would like to try something new and they won't be disappointed as it's really nicee and you can feel they have put so much efforts!! It's a good place to chill!!

Amazing place for a quiet and fine dine. Has Zomato gold 2 + 2 on drinks. There's match screening and a good amount of ambient music. The staff is very nice and polite. The food is quite tasty as well has a good amount of quantity especially the nachos and starters.

Great ambience, good quality projector screen, large group friendly, lovely chairs and seating arrangements but it's a big let down in terms of food. They don't have variety, what's available isn't  great plus it's expensive. Honestly, I tried to like their food (visited twice) but when they could not even get the Masala Papad right, I was convinced. Wish they'd look into this department and get it right, just like they got the ambience right. 

For me, this place is great just for having a couple of drinks. Enjoy your Zomato Gold or their local offer for that day.

It's a café located amidst the hustle bustle of Starbucks and CCD, if you are looking for a tranquil spot with good music and excellent ambience this is the place! The food was really delicious, MUST TRY THEIR MIX SAUCE PASTA. Every bite was "omg" with such a rich flavour! Not Ur indianised pasta with processed cheese gratings. Overall it was a wonderful experience! Loved the place and the food

A place with classy ambience and great variety of food, this place is near to nahur station and on the main streets of goregaon-mulund link round,
Runwals is second food hub of mulund with many food cafe over here and many more are coming soon and this one from them,

restaurants.address: Jalaram Commercial Complex, Saki Vihar Rd, Ansa Industrial Estate, Chandivali, Saki Naka, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400072, India

reviews.text: Rooftop is good with an open bar and a large projector screen for sports matches. The lower floors are really shady and the possibilities of you passing out on the floor are greater than normal due to the pitch black lighting.

This place is awesome. This is open roof place. The food here is simply awesome. Just the service is bit bad. U can try food whatever you want veg or non veg both are equally tasty. We tried few starters here all were very good in taste and they were served really nice. Ambience is very nice. Music is good and relaxing. The only think we doesn't like is the people who smoke because it makes uncomfortable.

Great place to have a party. Good ambience and well maintained. Great staff which gives a quick response. The food is well prepared. The drinks menu has variety and is affordable. The Sound system is great and the light is same. Sitting area is also nice. Great place. Starter and food takes less time to get served. Three layers of area including sitting, dancing and Smoking area as well. This place also has a parking spot which is the main thing a bar has to have.

AMBIENCE:

The entrance is quite cool with posters and frames on walls. The graffiti on walls are very attractive. The lightings are not as good for taking pictures. Overall its good.

FOOD: 

The quality of food as compared to the amount we are paying is too low. Even the taste was not as good as other bar provides. They usually takes time to prepare but the wait isn't worth. 

BAR:

The bar has good menu options with various types of alcohols been served. The beer quality doesn't fit with your regular taste. I was not feeling like having it. So think before ordering.

SHEESHA: They have herbal sheesha. Mostly it doesn't create much smoke but is good as compared to other sheeshas.
They have an hour limit for each pot. It was nice.

PRICE:

Everything is overpriced plus additional taxes are imposed. A small redbull can costed us around ₹220. All other food items were heavily charged. For no taste we paid excessively high amount. Totally dissatisfied with their pricing system. 

SERVICE:

Service was very prompt and the persons were very polite and well mannered. They obeyed properly and served professionally. 9/10 for them. 

Overall experience:

First of all, the main factor is price and food. I was disappointed by both. There was no proper taste or flavour in food. Paying more for those were other issue. So, I don't recommend anyone to go here unless it's urgency for you. There are several more in area which gives best service.

Lovely place to hang out with friends and party. Awesome music 👌. There's place for private party as well. They have a great rooftop seating too.
Now coming to food.
The cocktails were amazing!
Starters we're too good. Both veg and non veg.
We enjoyed the chicken sizzler for main course.
They also have a wide variety of options for desserts.
Over all drinks and food, both are great in this place.
It's a must visit place for weekends.

reviews.text:
5 Spice Missing on spice
The food that we ordered was pathetic and not worth the money. We have had food at 5 spice a couple of times but this time the food was worst. I placed the order at 10.30pm on the 23rd of August and we ate the food at 1.30am. The next day when I called 5 spice letting them know how tasteless the food was they stated that you should have called on the same  every day.when I already told him that we had the food at 1.30am. Later he tells me that you should have called before 12.00pm because the chef's were there till that time and only then this feedback/complain would have been considered. He also stated that we do not have a manager present at the moment and are working with minimum staff. I did tell him then why did you take the order when you guy's can't keep up to the mark of providing good food and service. When I told him that I will put my reviews he was all OK about it. This was the worst experience ever in terms of food and service. Will order food from small Chinese stalls hence forth.

The food was very tasty and the staff was very friendly... And the price was not very heavy on the pocket. The ambiance of the place was also very nice for family's and also had a trendy crowd... Overall a good experience. A must try place if you are a foodie..

The best place to eat Chinese and thai food. The quantity is huge so order accordingly. The taste is great and suits Indian taste buds. 5 spice noodles will never disappoint. You should also try rocky road and mission impossible desserts. They are finished quickly so reserve once before ordering main course.

Nice place to hang out with friends or family. Great food at a great price. Completely worth the money. Authentic Chinese cuisine. Desserts here are without a doubt one of the best things a person van have. If you ever come to Sakinaka, this is a must-try place.

The food was pathetic and not worth the money. We have had food at 5 spice many times but this time the food was worst. I  placed the order at  10.30pm on the 23rd of August and we ate the food at 1.30am. The next day when I called 5 spice letting them know how tasteless the food was they stated that you should have called the same day when I had already told him that we had the food at 1.30am. Later he tells me that you should have called before 12.00pm only then he would have considered because I called him at 2.00pm the next day. He also stated that we do not have a manager and we have very less staffing. I did tell him then why did you take the order. When I told him that I will put my reviews he was all OK about it. This was the worst experience ever. Waste of money.

reviews.text:
It's been a while I visited this place but posting the review now.
Lovely ambience!!
Great food.
Most lovely staff ❤️ which reminds me of an incident.

I had a meeting at rosewood which didn't really go well, and it was so bad that anyone could tell by my face that something is wrong. Probably the staff noticed that too and smilingly gestured me to sit down, in seconds two of them came to clean the table, passed all the leftovers towards me, asked if I needed anything, although being part of their job, I could feel the extra warmth.

So kudos to the staff and thanks for the lovely gesture that day :)
First thing its purely vegetarian... Unlike d routine menu, it has varieties.... Value for money... Good quantity.... Freshly made bread is awesome... Service is superb...

It's a vegetarian continental restaurant.

The decor is very beautiful. Seating has variations and are very comfortable. They have a fireplace too.

Outside seating is also there. There is ample seating provided to sit and wait for your table. 

Drinks, cocktails and mock tails are available. The menu is quite big. The dessert section is equally impressive. Tiramisu, Blueberry cheese cake, skillet cookies, sizzling brownie and so much more.
 
The unique feature is the salad bar. You can choose ingredients to make your own salad.

There is small bakery upstairs. Our kids went to see it too. 

The service is quick and efficient. They kept clearing the tables as soon as we were done with the dish. The serving staff is very helpful and good natured.

Washroom is available.

It's on a little expensive side but you get equally tasty food.

Walk into this upscale vegetarian all-day dining restaurant and bar, and be treated to a wonderful fare for your taste buds! The staff is very friendly and skilled, starting with Anthony who literally treats you like close friends! Over three visits I am yet to be less than awed by even one single dish, starting from mocktails and soups, down to some amazing starters, excellent main course, and killer desserts. They also have a boulangerie inside for your baked staples to take home, and a salad bar. Recommended any time!
The best place on earth for a snack, breakfast, lunch or dinner. This awesome place is one of the best food makers and ambient places I have ever known

reviews.text:
The staff and ambience lives up to the Taj brand, creating a comfortable and pleasant dining experience. The table service is extremely attentive, and they have attention to details of your requests. 
-Live music was very good
- Apart from this, the buffet spread is not impressive. Despite many types of desserts, they are varying flavours of similar items. 
-Servive is somewhat slow

Cozy Bar. It looks part of Tiqri Restaurant. But it is a separate place at the end of Tiqri Restaurant. One has to walk through the seating area of Restaurant.

The bar has a nice cozy elevated seating. Has a good selection of spirits. Closes at 1130pm on Mondays and at 0130am on all other days.
Excellent place with clear view of Airport,  beautiful rooms and best hospitality as standard.

A perfect place to grab a coffee and a bite. Jayesh the manager and Bhakti, Varun and Rajnish all are very attentive to your needs. Inspite of going after a brunch the service was prompt. Ordered a masala chai, club sandwich which it’s superbly yummy and an Americano. Perfect for two to share. Will be back.

Food : it’s a different buffet with many novel items: full marks for the experience and experimentation 
Ambience: lovely!
Service : umm a tad slow! 3 out of 5 is being kind They did get their act together after a while 
The white wine served came from South Africa and was dry and excellent! Unfortunately the name escapes me! Elephant something...
The Sangria though was a let down! Had to set it aside! Just order simple red wine folks.
The starters good but did not relish the paneer much. Even in the main course it did nothing for me.
Liked their health station and the spectacled chef behind it, courteous and helpful! Made me a great salad and batter fried broccoli and potatoes 
The cheese counter and the dishes next to it were great esp the one with couscous! Took a double serving 
The mushroom chestnut preparation looked scary but made up in taste! 
Their curd rice too was good 
It being a veg day I did not taste the fish or chicken but my friend appreciated them
Had a great time

The staff is courteous and helpful and friendly. The food was great and the music was great. The DJ played lively music throughout.
Nice place. Will surely visit again.

One of the coolest club in Mumbai . Club vibes are so good and powerful . Clubs interior is so good and creative . Food are good service staff is so good very humble . 
Drinks are good if u have to spend good time in clubs please do visit in Bombay adda . Experience new vibes and good music . Try good food and great drinks .

So i have been to Bombay Adda quite a few times and i am in love with the place. It has roof top , indoor sitting perfect for all the moods and days. We ordered nachos, pasta and samosa hummus. Samosa hummus was mouth smacking, must try incase you a hummus person. Honestly pasta was not upto the mark, little sweet, something wrong with the sause.

reviews.text: Sameer and his team are a bunch of wonderful, hard working, highly skilled people. I got my hair treated with cysteine and I am so impressed.. they explained the different options available for my hair without being too pushy, which I really appreciate.. I highly recommend Kalista and will definitely come back next whenever I'm in town.
Very clean. Good service. Polite and talented staff.

Sameer and his team are absolutely fantastic. I visited the salon at the end of January while I was attending a wedding in Mumbai. I live in London and have been trying to find a hair stylist that would really just understand my hair and style it to sit well. #curlyhairproblems 

I didn’t even have to tell Sameer what I wanted! He just knew what to do and for the first time in years I am absolutely loving my hair! Thank you so much Sameer! May have to fly over every time I need a haircut 😂

I was very unhappy with his behaviour

Very very bad!!!😡they said they have masseur but hair stylist gave the massage👎! And it was so bad that my legs started paining.if u want money ask me I'll give you without any service but dont do this fraud!

reviews.text: Nice place to hang out with friends nice snacks variety Available
Gr8888 taste. Much better and improved taste spclly of shawarma. Chicken pizza ws yummy

Located just outside the Seawoods Railway Station perfect place to hangout with friends and family and have really delicious nonveg food at amazingly affordable price 
The service and staff were excellent and quite friendly. 
Starting with CHICKEN KHAPSA RICE, Half of the plate quantity is enough for three people. The dish had plain rice on the top and a layer of chicken gravy and egg at the bottom. They also served the Raita with it. Now coming to CHICKEN KHAPSA DELUXE RICE where the quantity is same as the Chicken Kahpsa Rice. For those prefer chinese can go for this as I found it better than the Chicken khapsa Rice coz It comes with a layer of chicken tikka topped with a layer of fried rice. And then comes the CHICKEN HAKKA NOODLES where the quantity is good enough for 2 medium eating people. Not to forget that it was delicious, not too oily and they served with shezwan chutney. In second visit i had CHICKEN TIKKA BIRIYANI and in this the quantity is enough for just one person served with Raita. It was awesome and spicy as expected. Not the best Ive had, but good none the less. Along with it i had DOUBLE CHICKEN DOUBLE CHEESE PERI PERI SHAWARMA which was cheesy and spicy and served with a mayonese layer on top. Most teenagers come here only for this. These. are one of the best you can get in Navi Mumbai. And lastly the COLD COFFEE which was chilled and thick and had perfectly strong flavour also was cheap and totally worth
Chicken shwarma and other eatables are tasty and most importantly it's hygienic

The ambience is really pretty with wide space couches for groups and normal seating for 2-4 people. I’ve been there for more than 4-5 times. This place serves one of the best Chicken shawarmas dipped in mayonnaise and fully covered with cheese. Beautifully served with fries. Chicken cheese Peri Peri Shawarma(90Rs) has been the best ever. This place also serves cute small sized Pizza with a valuable rate. Must visit this place again and again.

reviews.text: Breakfast is best here ...Misal & other dish are also must try ...

Food - 2/5
Ambience - 2/5
I had Daal Paalak Chawal, Mushroom crispy and chaas (Buttermilk).
Daal Paalak chawal was bland and was giving me taste of coriander more than daal or Paalak.
Mushroom crispy was typical desi chinese as mushrooms were made into pakores (bhajiya) and we're dipped in desi chinese coloured tangy sweet supposed to be chinese sauce!
It also had options of veg thali which I felt like tasting if at all I come here again by any random chance.
That thali had Vermicelli kheer (I was obviously peeking into other's tables and hence I know)! May be it's tasty , may be it's not! If anyone tries that, let me know!
Chaas or the Buttermilk was looking so thick and it was surprisingly so watery.. 🙊🙊 it was a nice jeera milky water i must say!
Ambience: premise is Nicely lit but it was hot inside. Really very hot and humid where outside weather was pleasant! So eating in hot and humid environment in a restaurant where I am paying for food and taxes as well is not my thing!
No washrooms in this restaurant, there is a public washroom in front of this!
This is right opposite to Sewree bus depot.
Card payments were accepted.
In and all, if I am to go again I would definitely hesitate unless am dying of hunger!

reviews.text:
Great and huge place located at Sion Koliwada with comfort sitting arrangement famous for its Chinese, Mughlai, North Indian and Sea food.

In Mocktail drinks i ordered as follows...

1)Strawberry Delight.
2)Cranberry Cooler.

Strawberry Delight was properly made got the taste of Strawberry and was good in taste.

Cranberry delight was perfectly made and was very refreshing as well as taste.

In food i ordered....

1)Mutton Bhara.
2)Hardeep Punjab Special Mushroom Tikka.
3)Mutton Peshwari.
4)Jeera Rice.

Mutton bhara presentation was good Mutton was properly coocked and was soft and its taste was up to the mark.

Hardeep Punjab Special Mushroom tikka its presentation was great mushrooms were quit big in size and filled with cheese that was awesome in taste.

Mutton peshwari was cooked well served 4 pieces of mutton with gravy was enough for 2 person. Mutton pieces were soft and taste of gravy was delicious.

Jeera rice was well made rice was of good quality and was very tasty enjoyed it. 

In Desserts i ordered Slice kulfi that was very yummy in taste.

Ambiance was awesome service was good staff were polite and very friendly neat and clean place.

Must visit once.

A place with comfortable seating arrangements. More of white background. A place that serves varieties of cuisines. Chinese as well as Indian preferably North Indian cuisine, Mughlai dishes, and of course sea food too. 

I visited the place on Friday evening and it was all packed by 9 pm. More of a family restaurant. I saw many a families having dinner there. 

Generally I prefer to have non veg food but looking at a delicious menu here, I tried all vegetarian food and it was awesome. Appetizer as well as main course were delicious. 

Tried a few mocktails and they were worth every penny you would end up paying. 

Pinacolada: My usual drink. When in confusion, choose pinacolada. They had it perfectly. The blend was proportionate in a perfect way. Pineapple with coconut. Vanilla ice cream. 

Fruit punch: Mix of fruits. I requested them to make it without sugar syrup and they rightly did so. Refreshing. Fresh fruits. One of the best fruit punch preparations, I had in recent time. A bit tangy. 

The staff is very cooperative and helped me in deciding my orders. 

Tandoor broccoli and paneer: Generally, these two are different dishes: tandoor paneer and tandoor broccoli. I requested them to have it combined and they obliged it happily. Served with green chutney and red sauce. Perfectly grilled veggies. Delicious. Luscious paneer. Broccoli too was delicious. Paneer topped with cheese and coriander. Broccoli also topped with coriander. Onion slaw topped with mint and lemon. Broccoli had mustard feel as it was marinated with mustard sauce. Paneer was grilled along with onion, capsicum, and pineapple. 

Hara bhara kebab with galouti kebab: Melting kebabs. Galouti kebabs were better than hara bhara kebab but again this is sin comparing two food dishes, isn't it? Loved both the kebabs. Served with tomato sauce. Galouti kebab were made from beetroot. Filled with cheese and cream. 

In main course, we had tawa mushroom along with chura paratha. 

Tawa mushroom was cooked properly. Fresh mushroom. Gravy was perfectly fine. Goes well with chura paratha. Mushroom gravy had capsicum, bell peppers. Topped with coriander. Red gravy. Delicious. Paratha was something unique, it was more like warqi paratha. 

In dessert, we had gulab jamun rabdi. Delicious rabdi topped with gulab jamun. Perfectly sweetened rabdi. Loved the dessert too. Chilled rabdi served with hot gulab jamun. Topped with dry fruits. 

Overall, this is a nice place. The food is good. They have given emphasis on hygiene also. Cleanliness was upto the mark.

Longing for lip smacking Punjabi food then hardeep Punjab is perfect place to have delicious authentic Punjabi as well as north Indian Chinese as a well as mughlai food .
I was with my Friend .
The place is very huge I loved the way they have utilized the space .
Seating is so comfortable decor is done well .
Staff is courteous they helped us to choose the best .
The mocktails and food which we tried were ..
Mocktails: 
Cool blue and virgin pinacolada 
The mocktails was chilled ad refreshing the taste was very good.
I personally recommend cool blue .
Appetizer: 
Chaska maska chicken tikka:
It was suggested by there staff and we decided to try it out .
Well coming to the presentation it was cooked and severed in clay pot .and it tasted amazingly delicious I never had something like that before .
The chicken places were so juicy and tender It just got melted in mouth .this hi highly recommend dish .
Tiranga chicken tikka:
This dish looks so inviting and it tasted really good.
Chicken tikka prepared is three spices one of them is malai tikka ,pudina tikka and regular chicken tikka.each of them were rightly spiced.
In main course we ordered :
Chicken tikka masala which was served with butter kulcha it was so tasty perfectly cooked the chicken pieces were so juicy . and the gravy was rich and creamy .
The butter kulchas was loaded with ample amount of butter on it .
It was superb combination .
Dessert :
Gulab jamun with rabadi this is the best dessert I had till date.
The rabdi was so creamy and moderately sweet it just won my heart.
Would definitely visit this place in future.

In Mumbai, Hardeep Punjab, Mini Punjab, Ram Punjab, Sher-e-Punjab... for me, these are doyens as far as authentic Punjabi Cusine is considered and treasure fond memories of my frequent visits.
The other day landed up at Hardeep for a takeaway, at GTB Nagar (Sion Koliwada).
While everything is great out here, my fav is the Butter Chicken with Garlic Nan. 
One dish at a time and enjoy every morsel.
A day well spent 💃🏼❤️😄
Best place to have a Punjabi Indian Food at affordable price. Please try their desserts you will definitely love it.  gulabjaam Rabdi is yummy...

reviews.text: Service in lockdown is very bad..... does not provide spoon tissue for take away even the container is very small.... staff also are very arrogant
Go here for the amazing taste, but forget your calorie counter behind as you will be having 50% butter! But trust me, it’s worth it!

In the current pandemic the queue system adopted by the restaurant is a joke. Social distancing apart the location of the place and the class of society and beggars and vagrants hanging around leaves you in doubt about the health issues.
It  was closed for the know reasons(covid-19)  .. but we stopped for water

Mumbai is known for street food and pav bhaji is one of the most popular dishes here. Nearest station is Mumbai Central. Located at Tardeo. Place is very famous and very small as well, I waited for almost 30min outside in queue and 15 min to get my order and offered seats on sharing basis, no customer service ! Make sure  you have enough free time as there you may face a long queue and waiting time . The service may seem a little bit slow Just because of the crowd but the quality of the food is graet . No  Ac . Tables are very congested can't even sit and eat with comfortable posture, but taste is wow ! Sardar is very old outlet dating back to 1966 and known for its delicious buttery pav bhaji. They have maintained the same taste since then and the outlet seems to be always crowded with people and on weekends you have to wait for a hour or so to get seats. Must recommend for someone who wants to try out one of the best Pav bhaji !! Good by taste with loads of butter. It is having good service but too much of waiting specially during weekends as process is one round for parcel and one for having it there. It also serve milkshakes but it's costlier than it should be . Limited parking place .
       Overall had an amazing experience over there and would love to visit this place again.

A great place to have some unusual Gujarati combination food. Very fresh and tasty. The portions are very small for the amount charged for each portion. But the quality and the taste superstars the charges. It’s s very popular joint for Gujaratis and attracts people. Be early to get s table or be prepared to wait to get a table and it’s worth a wait !

The price is also very reasonable what you is what you get. The staff service is excellent. The place is clean and always feels good be there.
Panki as usual was great. The chutney and Mirchi along with it is suoer. Paneer lifafa, wada pav needs a special mention too.

reviews.text:

The tried  grilled dumplings with Veg Monchow soup.They where amazing in taste.A very good restaurant with delicious taste.

Chicken tandoori ! Dragon rice ! Soup ! Everything had a great taste ! Also tried mojito which quite splendid ! We order two of them ! Even four of us together couldn't finish it ! Overall great place !

This place is very popular with all age groups including students and professional.
Chinese Lovers must visit this place as it offers plenty much variety of dishes. Place is always crowded but worth of visit. Has limited seating arrangement, so please prepare for waiting during peak hours. Food quality that I personally feel is moderate, however food quantity is judging it's cost. The only thing I didn't like is service, not satisfied with staff service. Overall experience was moderate, looking forward to taste this food again.

reviews.text: I went there with my friends. We had an amazing time over there. Place is very good. Ambience, Food everything is good. It has a dance floor with DJ. It has separate dedicated smoking room. Bouncers are there for safety, so no worries if anything happens over there. And you get drinks with reasonable price and there are offers too on some drinks which are limited to some time duration. Service is great. I enjoyed the dance floor.

Warehouse Lounge is a nice Disco Pub located near Tikuji Ni wadi.
Cover charges is Rs 2k for a couple, which needs to be used against drinks and food.

Ambience is nice. There is DJ and Dance Floor. 

Crowd is nice and they have many bouncers outside and inside the pub for security purposes.

Food quality is nice and at reasonable prices.

Early table booking is advisable, as it gets filled quickly. 
Please check out for Bollywood songs timings. Generally starts post 10 pm / 10:30 pm

Smoking
They have a separate room inside for Smoking purpose.

This is amongst must visit place on my recommendation list.

Nice ambience, Music 🎶 and food 🥘 .. Superb place to hangout with friends , it has good people around and a screen to watch sports 🏈.
During cricket matches it is crowded which adds fun to it.. 
Location at Kothari compound Thane west behind Dmart. 
Food is tasty 😋 and little expensive too. 
Waiter was courteous to take order. 
Interiors are also equally good.

The ambience is great. The food quantity is also good. On weekends it's crowded after 9 pm. Before going check what are the Happy Hours, when we went there on Saturday happy hours were till 9 pm. 
The service is good. But orders were delayed and the server was not attending our table after serving starters. Otherwise, the service was good. Staff is polite and friendly.
The Mud Cake is a must-try. 😍😍😍
We ordered Chicken Tikka Pizza, Chicken Pops.
Dj was only playing English Songs. Don't know if Bollywood songs are played.
Dance floor is lit after 10.30 pm.🤩

Its an awesome place.... very nice and beautifully decorated.... superb ambiance.... Delicious food with good quantity as well as quality..... There are some offers of drinks...on weekends that mean on Friday Saturday & Sunday  there is a huge crowd... if you want to go on weekends  must go before 8pm so you can get the table... Or you can call them n reserved your table by registering your name contact number and number of people you are coming.... And on weekends There is a entry fees for both couples and stagg after 8pm... Yes the entry fees can be redeemed inside on food and drinks you buy.... On some days there are special events like some special DJ nights, Ladies nights,etc... They also have page on Instagram you can also follow them there...

Visited Amar Fast Food as we were in the Sakinaka area and feeling a bit hungry
Sat outside as wanted to have a quick bite and leave . Outdoor seating was no frills ordinary seating 
Ordered idli sambhar which was decent and grilled veg sandwich which too was ok

Amar Juice Centre is simply value for money of you order the right things. I have been a regular here since the last two years as it's very close to my office and it has never failed to disappoint me. Their Pav Bhaji is my all time favourite. They also deliver food and their packaging is good. You can also try their south Indian dishes and Chinese options.

Good food, good quality, good ambience waiters are also good. Only vegetarian food is allowed. Little costly but have good tasty food.

They have AC and Non-AC place to eat. Limited dishes in veg.

Good tasty fast food variety. Pav Bhaji having good taste one must try.

Limited space for parking outside the hotel. Average waiting time.

reviews.text: This place is worth it in every aspect,give it ambiance or taste or food portion or price. We love garlic bread and mixed sauce penne pasta here. Pizza is also good.

This place was great. Dishes were tasty. Ambiance was amazing. 750 for 2 people. 
If you visit in group, it will cost around 250-300 per person.

Well I had expectations from this place as it was something new in town, a new concept.
Well the ambience maybe good but food wasn't.
Everything we ordered was okay okay. Not the taste I would expect from a restaurant.
It was average.

Review as per 11th Nov'18 visit. 

Dividing review is positive and negative points. 

New place must try once, later upto you. 

Positives 

1. Best place to hangout in ulhasnagar, kind of pub theme. 

2. Food taste was mast but i think quality was very superior.. Made of high quality material and oil. 

3. Tried panner chilly, schezwan rice.. Both as per expected. 

4. No alcohol. 

5. Huge variety of soft drinks, coffees and tea including green and harbel. 

6. Superb music and nice ambiance. 

7. Card payment accepted.

8. Best palce for young people.

Negatives:

2. Ordering time 15 mints.

Its quite good to enjoy with friends. You can have a great experience 😉

reviews.text:
I visited this place when it was newly opened. The entire theme of the restaurant is Post office theme. I'll breakdown my review in few pointers

Location: Pretty far from Vasai railway station. This is a good hotel for the locals who live nearby

Ambience: Great with good ventilation and seats. The restaurant also offers a music area where music is played in the evening. It also has bar area

Food: The food quality is good and tastes well. I have tried some of the things in the menu and it has not really disappointed me

Price: Fairly priced the food can come upto 1000 approx for two people. With drinks it would be extra

Parking: There is a big parking space available downstairs for both two and four wheelers

Overall review: Good for a weekend dinner. You can make reservations or walk in too. For certain occasions or festival do make reservations. The hotel is big enough to accommodate quite number of people. The staff is good and the hotel offers great value for money

3 STAR is for the ambience and the live music which goes on in the restaurant. Menu is too small to choose from. Service is Too quick might be because of less dishes. The taste of food in not as expected. They must improve the taste of their food.
This is yet the best restaurant in this location, has a variety if vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes. I had the post office platter here, and it was mouth watering. Surely recommend to visit here.

This place has been one of my fav hang out places.. the ambience here is absolutely perfect with the perfect blend of music and alcohol and food.. I mus say evy dish over here is worth trying esp the blanket prawns and the chicken sizzler.. the sizzler s absolutely refreshing with veggies and the chicken s perfectly cooked.. the concept of ice cream in a tea glass also s out of the box.. a place worth trying..

Great place to go with family and friends, good service and delicious food. Chicken chowpatti is a must try. 👍
Also, there is escalator and parking space available.

reviews.text: I normally rate the APMC market Bhagat Tarachand as the best. In fact, they are the original ones. But today was my first visit to them (while the lockdown is still in effect) and we got the parcels to it. The taste was right up there. The service was fast. The folks were polite and I would rate it highly. This is right inside Vashi which is pretty convenient for people as well. Recommended.

Bhagattarachand is famous for their veg mouthwatering dishes. They have so many branches all over the Mumbai. We visited their vashi branch during last year November on the special occasion of our 6 month wedding anniversary and it is very nice place to celebrate your special days. We have ordered veg spring roll in starter and it was very tasty and in the main course there was Garlic Naan, Kadhai Mashroom and Baby corn Masala, all the dishes are very delicious. which own my heart was  their special kulfi falooda, It is their best iteam in dessert. Must recommend place for the vegetarians if you are near to vashi, Navi Mumbai. The staffs are very helpful and they try to make your visit memorable. Ambience of the restaurant is normal. In vashi branch they have two floors, while ground floor is non AC and upper floor is fully air-conditioned and the price different for both the floor.
Home like food ,the food was quite awesome last time I came here with my friends
Its situated in sector 12 of vashi. Nice place for vegetarian meals. Very crowdy during weekends. Ac dining is also available. Its in the main road near the bus stop of kopri naka.
nice test food only vegitrian but price like non vag. Service good other all things are really very good for lunch and dinner, rice quality is good but quantity is very less

We went to this wonderful place the union bar and eating house. This place is so beautiful and the ambience is lovely you will surely fall in love with this place. The staff is well trained and friendly. They had a very good environment with a good music playing in the background. The chairs and the tables are very nice. restaurants.address: C18-21 Dalia Industrial Estate Near, Fun Republic Road, Off New Link Road, Veera Desai Industrial Estate, Andheri West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400053, India

reviews.text: Doolally taproom is a great place to catch up with your friends and grab some freshly brewed beer. Their menu includes comfy food and the quantity and taste of the food was amazing. It has a cozy ambience with calm music and they also have free to play games like jenga, monopoly and other card and board games which will help you have a fun time with your friends. They have indoor as well as outside seating. The best part about this place is that it's pet friendly. So you don't have to leave your pet at home by himself, he can just tag along and play with other pets here, the menu also has a special section for pet food.

This is a really great place to enjoy some delicious craft beers. If you're one of those beer people then this is a place you certainly shouldn't miss out on. You have a decent variety of craft beers to choose from. The apple cider is one of the popular choices. Not only are the beers good but the snacks are equally good too. The potato fries are served with a variety of dips which is a must try. And to add to it you have various board games to choose from to enjoy with friends. The entire ambiance and the food adds to the experience. Really good place to visit with a group of friends.
The food tastes great and the prices are quite feasible! They have special offers in the month of October, especially on the beers.

I am used to visiting Doolally at Palm Beach Road, Navi Mumbai. So visiting this one was a good change for me. The only issue I faced was that the premises outside the pub were unhygienic. Apart from that, this is a great plea and I will definitely recommend!

*Flavoured Beer*
Try their apple/mango cider with house fries.
They offer drinks which is best in town which includes 
-apple cider
-mango cider
-stout beer
-Belgian wit
-pale ale
 and various more depending upon stocks and availability.
This place is pet friendly and pet food is also served here.
Very delightful and happening place at Andheri West. I was amazed to taste beers that too of fruit flavours and it’s definitely worth it for especially those who make wacky faces when it comes to drinking beer.
Cheers!

Amazing vibe you will get at this place and the food my good it's amazing. Good place to chill out with your buddies after a tiring day. Located at one of the best place. Not to far, not to near. And the hygiene and everything is maintained with smoking room inside. Amazing place must say. I loved the food.

Huge space, good food however slightly high on price. Is usually crowded on Friday nights so prior booking is recommended. The dance floor gets really pumped up later in the evening. They have some good world cup offers on right now. Should visit for an evening with your squad.

A awesome place for party lovers and group parties, place has a classic bar room with dance floor, good food & DJ rocks with all the grooving tracks, Fun loving people's adda so having a fun frolic night life with this outlet

reviews.text: Quality food and a good place for team dinner. Interior are also great to click photos

A pretty chill place for friends and family to hang out with a few drinks. The happy hours have 1+1 like most restaurants. Best time to visit would be after 6pm in the evening as they have amazing music and a very lively vibe. The food is good. If you're lucky there are complimentary drinks (shots) for the women on the table which was a cherry on the cake🔥. All in all a good experience. Timbuctoo is located right on top of Pop Tates and the entry is through the Pop Tates premise.

Lively, crowded, reasonably priced and fantastic service. Definitely a great place to go with friends and family. 

One thing that impressed me was that there was a janitor permanently stationed at the washrooms to clean them after every visit! I sincerely believe that the easiest way to know how well a business is run is to visit the loo.... And these loos were PERFECT!

Heartily recommended.

This place has been around for quite sometime now. Service is good and food tastes wonderful. The pizzas are quite amazing and overall it doesn't affect your wallet much.
The ambience is calm and delightful. During early evenings it's quite pleasant.
On the top floor you have Timbuctoo and on the ground floor you have Pop Tate's. Both have different menu although kitchen is the same
Great place with great ambience try visit during happy hour to enjoy more

Dishes here r the best.

reviews.text: Pretty good place for family dining together services are good and environment is pleasant
Limited menu but good food...service quality is not so great

My first experience with Gujurati cuisine and the verdict is...fantastic!!!  I was on the fence as to whether I should visit Gujurat, but if they cook like the chefs at Nimantran, I'm definitely going to go.  The menu is simple, there's a thali, but there's such variety with sweet, savory and spicy.  And it's a subtle spiciness so if you're a white person like me, don't be turned away.  Its 325 rupees for an all you can eat thali at dinner time, and the owner and staff were really welcoming and friendly guys.  I arrived at 7 on the dot so I had some time alone to talk with them and they answered any questions I had about any of the new exotic dishes.
Lovely unlimited thali, reasonable pricing. Service is leisurely, which might not be to everyone's liking.
Good though fairly simple thali. And not really expensive. Just about Rs325 pp. Strangely not crowded on a Friday afternoon except for a large group of elderly women.

The club is very good as it is said to be the best club of the city . The DJ was good but by saying Bollywood night , they started Bollywood @11:00 . And many times the DJ was doing over remixes because of which the joyness of original song got destroyed . Otherwise the club is very spacious and awesome but a little expensive . Unfortunately They don't serve breezer and vodka . I am little disappointed by the availability of food 
Mumbai's standards. Double ceiling roof, well lit and great music system.
Of course it will come with a price, drinks are costly and so is a table if you don't fancy the idea of dancing for long or want to take a pause.
Whole place is divided in half, the other half is seems a private place. On a Saturday night People start coming around 11 and its good number of people who visit.
Trendy, late-night club offering cocktails & global fare, plus lively DJs, dancing & VIP 
1.Entry fees is 3000 rupees.
2. Once you go inside you can not go out and re enter.
3. There is no single chair to sit.
4. Drinks costs avarage 1000 rupees plus service charge 10% plus VAT plus 2xGST. Photo of a bill is shared.
5. The music is trance and very loud. Neither you can dance on it nor you can talk to your friends/Partner
6. I could see barely 18 year old teens inside the club which made me uncomfortable.
7. Club is divided into two. To enter the half where crowd is less and has seating arrangement, you have to pay hefty.
8. If you want to sit at crowded area, you have to pay a big amount to book a chair.
Superb music superb vibes electric atmosphere on weekends that continues till 4 am in the morning. Visited this pub on a Saturday night. Entry was 3000 (Cover Charge) for couple, Food and drinks were fine, service was a bit slow but when you are in such an electric atmosphere dont realy care, Overall a 3/5 for food n service but a 5+ for the you atmosphere.
